upplied%20to%20Ukraine%20%E2%80%94%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-has-sent-hundreds-of-phoenix-ghost-drones-to-ukraine-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_top%5C%22%3EPhoenix%20Ghost%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-sends-ukraine-loitering-drones-for-kamikaze-attacks-on-russia-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_top%5C%22%3ESwitchblade%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20could%20get%20a%20new%20mission%3A%20hunting%20Russian%20nukes%20in%20Kaliningrad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EDrones%20vs.%20nukes%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russia%20S-400%20Kaliningrad%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5cdae14a021b4c63a32cf372%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22813%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ES-400%20surface-to-air%20missile%20systems%20at%20a%20military%20base%20in%20Kaliningrad%20in%20March%202019.%3Cp%3EREUTERS%2FVitaly%20Nevar%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EKaliningrad%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussias-kaliningrad-could-be-next-flashpoint-in-standoff-with-europe-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ekey%20military%20outpost%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0sandwiched%20between%20Lithuania%20and%20Poland%20on%20the%20Baltic%20coast.%20It%20has%20long%20hosted%20both%20nuclear%20and%20conventional%20forces%2C%20though%20Russia's%20military%20has%20moved%20several%20units%20based%20there%20to%20Ukraine%20since%20the%20fighting%20started%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKaliningrad's%20location%20allows%20the%20Kremlin%20to%20threaten%20several%20NATO%20members%20with%20long-range%20weapons%2C%20and%20it%20could%20be%20a%20base%20from%20which%20Russian%20forces%20could%20interfere%20with%20a%20NATO%20response%20to%20a%20clash%20with%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20chances%20of%20a%20war%20with%20Russia%20seem%20low%2C%20Kaliningrad%20still%20represents%20%26quot%3Ba%20major%20threat%26quot%3B%20to%20NATO%2C%20and%20the%20alliance%20need%20to%20invest%20in%20troops%20and%20weapons%20to%20neutralize%20Russian%20forces%20there%20in%20case%20of%20a%20conflict%2C%20William%20DiRubbio%2C%20a%20second%20lieutenant%20in%20the%20US%20Air%20Force%2C%20wrote%20in%20a%20recent%20article%20published%20by%20the%20journal%20of%20the%20Royal%20United%20Services%20Institute%2C%20a%20British%20think%20tank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDiRubbio%20argues%20that%20NATO%20could%20use%20special-operations%20forces%20to%20prevent%20Russia%20from%20launching%20the%20tactical%20nuclear%20weapons%20it%20has%20stored%20in%20Kaliningrad%20by%20targeting%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.19fortyfive.com%2F2023%2F06%2Fiskander-the-missile-putin-would-use-to-start-a-war-against-nato%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Iskander%20ballistic%20missiles%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20would%20likely%20carry%20those%20weapons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221196%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Iskander-M%20short-range%20ballistic%20missile%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5ae8d93a7708e9017b04b4b1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22794%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20Iskander-M%20short-range%20ballistic%20missile.%3Cp%3ERussian%20Defense%20Ministry%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGoing%20after%20the%20Russia's%20nuclear%20command-and-control%20infrastructure%20%26quot%3Bcould%20have%20immense%20deterrence%20and%20escalatory%20ramifications%26quot%3B%20and%20should%20be%20avoided%2C%20as%20should%20targeting%20the%20nuclear%20warheads%20themselves%2C%20but%20taking%20out%20the%20delivery%20platform%20would%20thwart%20Russian%20nuclear%20launches%2C%20according%20to%20DiRubbio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20Iskander%20missiles%20are%20mobile%2C%20special-operations%20troops%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bthe%20best%20method%20to%20deal%20with%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20DiRubbio%20writes%2C%20citing%20missions%20by%20the%20US%20Army's%20Delta%20Force%20and%20its%20British%20cousin%2C%20the%20Special%20Air%20Service%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdelta-force-sas-hunted-iraqi-scud-missiles-during-gulf-war-2021-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eto%20hunt%20down%20and%20destroy%20Iraq's%20Scud%20missiles%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0during%20the%20Gulf%20War%20as%20precedent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENATO%20forces%20could%20use%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkamikaze-style-drones-big-advantage-and-challenge-top-marines-say-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eloitering%20munitions%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20drones%20designed%20to%20linger%20near%20a%20target%20before%20crashing%20into%20and%20destroying%20it%20%E2%80%94%20for%20such%20a%20mission%20in%20Kaliningrad.%20%26quot%3BA%20focus%20should%20also%20be%20on%20the%20training%20of%20these%20forces%20with%20the%20Phoenix%20Ghost%20and%20Switchblade%20drones%20to%20assist%20them%20in%20their%20search%20and%20destroy%20efforts%2C%26quot%3B%20DiRubbio%20writes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpecial%20operators%20are%20trained%20to%20undertake%20such%20difficult%20missions%2C%20and%20one%20could%20see%20a%20Delta%20Force%20squadron%20armed%20with%20loitering%20munitions%2C%20also%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bkamikaze%20drones%2C%26quot%3B%20infiltrating%20Kaliningrad%20in%20order%20to%20do%20it.%20%26quot%3BTo%20enable%20quick%20action%20in%20the%20case%20of%20conflict%2C%20NATO%20ought%20to%20begin%20investment%20in%20small%20staging%20camps%20near%20Poland%20and%20Lithuania's%20respective%20border%20with%20Kaliningrad%2C%26quot%3B%20DiRubbio%20writes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESwitchblade%20and%20Phoenix%20Ghost%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Marine%20with%20a%20Switchblade%20drone%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F623b9f73ce16b60018edf65e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20US%20Marine%20prepares%20a%20Switchblade%20drone%20for%20launch%20during%20an%20exercise%20at%20Camp%20Lejeune%20in%20North%20Carolina%20in%20July%202021.%3Cp%3EUS%20Marine%20Corps%2FPfc.%20Sarah%20Pysher%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20has%20sent%20tens%20of%20billions%20of%20dollars%20in%20military%20aid%20to%20Ukraine%20and%20provided%20thousands%20of%20weapons%2C%20ranging%20from%20main%20battle%20tanks%20down%20to%20one-way%20attack%20drones%2C%20like%20the%20Switchblade%20and%20Phoenix%20Ghost%2C%20that%20a%20few%20soldiers%20can%20carry%20and%20operate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20relatively%20short%20range%2C%20these%20drones%20are%20designed%20to%20take%20out%20relatively%20small%20targets%20on%20the%20battlefield%2C%20whether%20its%20a%20few%20troops%20in%20a%20trench%20or%20an%20armored%20vehicle.%20The%20US%20has%20provided%20a%20few%20hundred%20of%20those%20two%20drones%20to%20Ukraine%2C%20including%20both%20version%20of%20the%20Switchblade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Switchblade%20300%20packs%20an%20explosive%20charge%20roughly%20equivalent%20to%20a%20Claymore%20anti-personnel%20mine%20to%20take%20out%20infantry%20targets.%20It%20is%20fired%20from%20a%20mortar-like%20tube%20and%20has%20a%20range%20of%206%20miles%2C%20though%20it%20can%20stay%20in%20the%20air%20for%20just%2015%20minutes.%20The%20Switchblade%20600%20is%20designed%20for%20heavy-duty%20targets%2C%20like%20tanks%2C%20and%20packs%20an%20explosive%20charge%20similar%20to%20that%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjavelins-stingers-nlaws-help-ukraine-destroy-russian-tanks-aircraft-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJavelin%20anti-tank%20missile%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20has%20a%20range%20of%2024%20miles%20and%20can%20stay%20in%20the%20air%20for%20about%2040%20minutes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELittle%20is%20known%20about%20the%20capabilities%20of%20the%20Ph