-370-case-supreme-court-asks-jk-administration-236345%3Finfinitescroll%3D1%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20academic%20had%20taken%20leave%20for%20two%20days%20to%20appear%20in%20the%20matter%20and%20had%20been%20suspended%20on%20his%20return.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20unfair%2C%20I%20am%20sure%20the%20AG%20will%20look%20at%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sibal%20was%20quoted%20by%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChief%20Justice%20of%20India%20(CJI)%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20told%20AG%20R.%20Venkataramani%20to%20look%20into%20the%20matter%20when%20solicitor%20general%20Tushar%20Mehta%20interjected%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fwhy-lecturer-suspended-soon-after-appearing-in-article-370-case-supreme-court-asks-jk-administration-236345%3Finfinitescroll%3D1%5C%22%3Esaying%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20checked%20up%20after%20having%20read%20in%20the%20newspapers.%20What%20is%20reported%20in%20the%20newspapers%20may%20not%20be%20the%20whole%20truth.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESibal%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20August%2025%20order%20made%20a%20reference%20to%20Bhatt%E2%80%99s%20appearance%20in%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Farticle-370-hearing-day-9-extreme-examples-extreme-cases%5C%22%3EArticle%20370%20Hearing%3A%20SC%20Told%20Extreme%20Examples%20Are%20Necessary%20To%20Solve%20Extreme%20Cases%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMehta%20argued%20that%20Bhatt%20appears%20in%20various%20courts%20and%20that%20there%20were%20%E2%80%9Cother%20issues%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CThen%20he%20should%20have%20been%20suspended%20earlier%2C%20why%20now%3F%20This%20is%20not%20fair.%20This%20is%20not%20the%20way%20democracy%20should%20function%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sibal%20responded.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTalk%20to%20the%20Lieutenant%20Governor%20and%20see%20what%20has%20happened.%20If%20there%20is%20something%20apart%20from%20this%2C%20then%20it%20is%20different.%20But%20why%20this%20in%20close%20succession%20to%20him%20appearing%20in%20the%20matter%3F%E2%80%9D%20CJI%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Kishan%20Kaul%20said%20that%20if%20the%20letter%20of%20suspension%20has%20reference%20to%20his%20appearance%2C%20then%20%E2%80%9Cthere%20is%20a%20problem%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhat%20happens%20to%20so%20much%20freedom%3F%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20B.%20R.%20Gavai%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBhatt%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fkashmiri-lecturer-suspended-after-appearing-in-supreme-court-for-article-370-hearing%5C%22%3Ehad%20appeared%20before%20the%20court%20on%20August%2024%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20was%20suspended%20the%20next%20day.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20a%20challenging%20situation%20for%20educators%20like%20me%20when%20we%20teach%20the%20principles%20of%20this%20beautiful%20constitution%20and%20the%20ideals%20of%20democracy%20to%20our%20students%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%20Students%20often%20pose%20a%20difficult%20question%20%E2%80%93%20are%20we%20still%20a%20democracy%20after%20the%20events%20of%20August%2C%202019%3F%20Answering%20this%20question%20becomes%20extremely%20complex%20and%20challenging%20for%20me%2C%E2%80%9D%20Bhatt%20had%20said%20in%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693219510000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-asks-ag-to-look-into-suspension-of-jk-lecturer-after-his-appearance-in-article-370-hearing%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20difficult%20to%20teach%20the%20ideals%20of%20democracy%20to%20our%20students%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%E2%80%9D%20Zahoor%20Ahmad%20Bhatt%20had%20said%20in%20court%20a%20day%20before%20his%20suspension.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22American%20homes%20are%20shrinking%2C%20but%20it%20isn't%20making%20houses%20any%20more%20affordable%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20small%2C%20light%20blue%20house%20with%20a%20red%20door%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63e2b0d327e5db0018ee9b33%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELike%20other%20government-backed%20loans%2C%20FHA%20interest%20rates%20are%20typically%20lower%20than%20conventional%20loan%20rates.%3Cp%3Eirina88w%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ENew-unit%20sizes%20for%20homes%20have%20decreased%2013%25%20nationally%20since%202015%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Census%20Bureau.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EYet%2C%20the%20cost%20per%20square%20foot%20has%20markedly%20accelerated%20over%20the%20same%20period%2C%20data%20from%20John%20Burns%20Research%20and%20Consulting%20shows.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBuilders%20are%20reducing%20square%20footage%20by%20deducting%20extra%20bedrooms%20and%20bathrooms.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20average%20size%20of%20a%20home%20in%20the%20US%20is%20steadily%20decreasing.%20And%20unfortunately%2C%20prices%20are%20continuing%20to%20rise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECensus%20data%20shows%20that%20the%20median%20square%20footage%20of%20floor%20area%20for%20single-family%20starts%20in%20the%20US%20peaked%20at%202%2C519%20during%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%202015%2C%20and%20has%20since%20dropped%2013%25%20to%202%2C191%2C%20as%20of%20the%20second%20quarter%20of%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20cost%20per%20square%20foot%20has%20been%20rising.%20From%201992%20to%202021%2C%20the%20measure%20increased%20by%20about%201%25%20annually%20on%20an%20inflation-adjusted%20year-over-year%20basis%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20John%20Burns%20Research%20and%20Consulting%20(%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjbrec.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJBREC%3C%2Fa%3E).%20That's%20accelerated%20to%2013%25%20in%202021%2C%20and%2010%25%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHome%20prices%20just%20soared%2C%26quot%3B%20Chris%20Porter%2C%20senior%20VP%20and%20chief%20demographer%20for%20JBREC%2C%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThe%20demand%20for%20housing%20during%20the%20pandemic%20years%20was%20just%20skyrocketing.%20We%20saw%20increased%20prices%20across%20the%20board%2C%20and%20that's%20showing%20up%20in%20that%20increased%20price%20per%20square%20foot.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPut%20simply%2C%20new%20homeowners%20are%20getting%20less%20bang%20for%20their%20buck.%20While%20settling%20for%20smaller%20homes%20has%20helped%20many%20buyers%20fit%20into%20their%20desired%20price%20range%2C%20they're%20still%20paying%20a%20premium%20compared%20to%20recent%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20all%20happening%20at%20a%20time%20when%2C%20by%20one%20measure%2C%20overall%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fhousing-market-unaffordable-mortgage-rates-home-prices-inventory-2008-crisis-2023-8%5C%22%3Ehome%20affordability%20is%20its%20lowest%20since%202006%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20even%20worse%20than%20during%20the%20Global%20Financial%20Crisis.%20The%20major%20culprit%20is%20a%20mix%20of%20rising%20home%20prices%2C%20an%20inventory%20shortage%2C%20and%20the%20highest%2030-year%20mortgage%20rates%20in%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20really%20comes%20down%20to%20the%20demand%2C%26quot%3B%20Porter%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20was%20so%20much%20demand%20for%20housing%20these%20last%20several%20years%2C%20and%20we%20saw%20continued%20price%20increases%20through%202021%2C%20and%20early%202022%2C%20the%20builders%20were%20raising%20prices%20and%20there%20was%20such%20strong%20demand%20that%20people%20were%20continuing%20to%20pay%20for%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMortgage%20rates%20were%20at%20such%20historical%20lows%20during%202021%20and%202022%20that%20buyers%20are%20unlikely%20to%20trade%20their%20homes%20bought%20during%20that%20time%20for%20new%20ones%20due%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcommodities%2Fhousing-market-outlook-mortgage-applications-rates-fed-home-prices-property-2023-8%3F_gl%3D1*15ztybk*_ga*MTY2Njk0NjcyOS4xNjg4MzkwODMw*_ga_E21CV80ZCZ*MTY5Mjk4NDA3OS4zNi4xLjE2OTI5ODQwOTAuNDkuMC4w%5C%22%3Erates%20now%20being%20in%20the%207%25%20range%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Porter%20said.%20Homeowners%20holding%20onto%20homes%20led%20to%20a%20lack%20of%20inventory%20%E2%80%94%20which%20runs%20up%20the%20cost%20of%20homes%20on%20the%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Redfin%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.redfin.com%2Fus-housing-market%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20median%20sale%20price%20of%20a%20home%20increased%3C%2Fa%3E%2046%25%20from%20July%202018%20to%202023%20%E2%80%94%20from%20%24288%2C203%20to%20%24422%2C137.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20are%20prices%20per%20square%20foot%20going%20up%2C%20data%20suggests%20that%20contractors%20are%20less%20likely%20to%20build%20homes%20with%20a%20lower%20price%20per%20square%20foot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEstridge%20Homes%2C%20a%20homebuilder%20based%20out%20of%20Indiana%2C%20recently%20introduced%20detached%20homes%20300%20to%20500%20feet%20smaller%20than%20its%20normal%20builds%2C%20and%20%2450%2C000%20to%20%2475%2C000%20cheaper.%20The%20homebuilder%20is%20downsizing%20new%20units%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Feconomy%2Fhousing%2Fhome-prices-mortgage-rates-smaller-houses-34e06123%3Fmod%3Dhp_lead_pos8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egetting%20rid%20of%20some%20bedrooms%20and%20bathrooms%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.zillow.com%2Fresearch%2Fnew-construction-smaller-homes-32892%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESingle-family%20home%20starts%20with%20less%20than%20three%20bedrooms%3C%2Fa%3E%20increased%209.