t%20systems%20that%20contribute%20to%20a%20brighter%20future.%20Kudos%20to%20your%20creative%20and%20thoughtful%20approach!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20a%20thoughtful%20idea%2C%20sir!%20Promoting%20chess%20and%20supporting%20parents%20who%20nurture%20their%20children's%20passions%20is%20truly%20commendable.%20This%20gesture%20aligns%20perfectly%20with%20the%20spirit%20of%20investing%20in%20a%20brighter%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20third%20user%20wrote.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693219200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fi8s3n99_praggnanandhaa-with-mother_625x300_28_August_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Foffbeat%2Fdeserve-our-gratitude-anand-mahindra-to-gift-praggnanandhaas-parents-an-electric-car-4336128%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Several%20people%20on%20Twitter%20urged%20Mr%20Mahindra%20to%20gift%20Thar%20to%20Praggnanandhaa%20for%20his%20runner-up%20finish%20at%20the%20FIDE%20Chess%20World%20Cup.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Foffbeat%2Fdeserve-our-gratitude-anand-mahindra-to-gift-praggnanandhaas-parents-an-electric-car-4336128%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Foffbeat%2Fdeserve-our-gratitude-anand-mahindra-to-gift-praggnanandhaas-parents-an-electric-car-4336128%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Foffbeat%2Fdeserve-our-gratitude-anand-mahindra-to-gift-praggnanandhaas-parents-an-electric-car-4336128%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20What%20BRICS%2C%20Now%20%26quot%3BG11%26quot%3B%2C%20Means%20For%20The%20West%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20expansion%20of%20BRICS%20has%20considerable%20geopolitical%20significance.%20It%20is%20a%20consequential%20step%20forward%20in%20changing%20the%20balance%20between%20the%20West%20and%20others%20in%20the%20global%20system.%20The%20number%20of%20countries%20from%20the%20Global%20South%20that%20formally%20applied%20for%20BRICS%20membership%20or%20showed%20interest%20in%20joining%20the%20grouping%20indicates%20a%20growing%20discontent%20with%20the%20West-dominated%20global%20order%20that%20continues%20to%20be%20shaped%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20policy%20priorities%20and%20interests%20of%20the%20major%20Western%20powers.%20The%20Global%20South%20wants%20greater%20democratisation%20of%20international%20relations%20and%20an%20enhancement%20of%20its%20role%20in%20global%20mechanisms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20signifies%20a%20rejection%20of%20the%20West's%20policies%20towards%20both%20Russia%20and%20China%2C%20of%20the%20narrative%20that%20Russia's%20military%20intervention%20in%20Ukraine%20and%20China's%20hegemonic%20ambitions%20threaten%20the%20existing%20global%20order%2C%20and%20that%20the%20global%20ideological%20conflict%20is%20between%20democracies%20and%20autocracies.%20This%20can%20be%20concluded%20from%20the%20rush%20to%20join%20BRICS%20while%20the%20conflict%20in%20Ukraine%20continues%20and%20despite%20its%20damaging%20consequences%20for%20the%20developing%20world%20by%20way%20of%20disruption%20of%20food%2C%20fertiliser%2C%20and%20energy%20supplies%20and%20price%20rise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20push%20for%20opening%20the%20doors%20to%20BRICS%20has%20certainly%20come%20from%20China%20and%20Russia.%20The%20global%20system%20is%20under%20new%20stresses%20with%20the%20collapse%20of%20Russia's%20ties%20with%20the%20US%20and%20Europe%20and%20the%20rise%20of%20serious%20tensions%20between%20the%20US%20and%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETies%20between%20Russia%20and%20the%20West%20will%20take%20a%20long%20time%20to%20repair.%20Western%20sanctions%20against%20Russia%20will%20not%20be%20rolled%20back%20in%20the%20foreseeable%20future%20unless%20there%20is%20a%20radical%20political%20change%20in%20Russia%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20West%2C%20which%20is%20most%20unlikely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20now%20sees%20the%20rise%20of%20China%20as%20a%20threat%20to%20its%20global%20supremacy.%20It%20is%20seeking%20to%20thwart%20China's%20technological%20progress%2C%20as%20it%20is%20in%20the%20advanced%20and%20critical%20technology%20areas%20that%20power%20contestations%20lie%20in%20the%20future.%20The%20US%20will%20prefer%20to%20achieve%20its%20goals%20without%20direct%20military%20conflict%20with%20either%20Russia%20or%20China%2C%20but%20it%20is%20strengthening%20its%20alliances%20in%20Europe%20and%20Russia%20as%20a%20deterrence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20US%20policy%20is%20bringing%20Russia%20and%20China%20closer%20together%20strategically.%20The%20imbalance%20of%20power%20between%20Russia%20and%20China%20is%20growing.%20China%20has%20become%20the%20largest%20manufacturing%20power%20in%20the%20world%20and%20the%20biggest%20exporter.%20It%20is%20technologically%20advanced%20in%20many%20areas%20and%20controls%20the%20supply%20chains%20in%20some%20critical%20technologies%20and%20raw%20materials.%20Russia%20has%20huge%20natural%20resources%20and%20is%20a%20formidable%20nuclear%20power%2C%20but%20its%20small%20population%20and%20a%20shrunk%20manufacturing%20base%20are%20a%20handicap.%20In%20many%20advanced%20technology%20areas%20such%20as%20telecommunications%2C%20renewable%20energy%2C%20electrical%20vehicles%2C%20etc.%20it%20is%20not%20in%20the%20race%20with%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENevertheless%2C%20Russia%20and%20China%20combined%20present%20a%20formidable%20challenge%20to%20Western%20power.%20Together%20they%20dominate%20the%20Eurasian%20continent.%20They%20are%20now%20conducting%20joint%20naval%20exercises%20in%20the%20western%20Pacific%20and%20even%20the%20Mediterranean%20as%20a%20political%20signal.%20They%20oppose%20the%20Indo-Pacific%20concept%20and%20the%20Quad.%20They%20cooperate%20in%20the%20UN%20Security%20Council%20against%20Western%20moves%20when%20required.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia%20and%20China%20want%20to%20reduce%20the%20hegemony%20of%20the%20US%20dollar%2C%20to%20which%20end%20they%20are%20trading%20in%20each%20other's%20currencies.%20Eighty%20per%20cent%20of%20their%20bilateral%20trade%20is%20today%20in%20their%20national%20currencies.%20President%20Putin%20has%20long%20argued%20in%20favour%20of%20a%20BRICS%20reserve%20currency%2C%20though%20it%20is%20not%20an%20easily%20achievable%20objective.%20What%20is%20more%20feasible%2C%20and%20is%20happening%20already%2C%20is%20for%20the%20BRICS%20countries%20to%20trade%20with%20each%20other%20in%20their%20national%20currencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPresident%20Lula%20has%20voiced%20the%20growing%20mood%20by%20asking%20why%20Brazil%20and%20China%20have%20to%20trade%20with%20each%20other%20in%20US%20%24%20and%20not%20in%20their%20own%20currencies.%20Lula's%20proposal%20is%20to%20create%20a%20payment%20method%20independent%20of%20the%20dollar%20to%20be%20worked%20out%20with%20the%20help%20of%20the%20BRICS%20Bank%2C%20whose%20chairman%20is%20Dilma%20Rousseff.%20India%20too%20is%20seeking%20to%20use%20the%20Indian%20rupee%20in%20trading%20with%20some%20of%20its%20partners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussian%20Foreign%20Minister%20Sergey%20Lavrov%20in%20his%20press%20conference%20in%20Johannesburg%20on%20August%2024%20put%20the%20project%20of%20a%20BRICS%20reserve%20currency%20in%20perspective.%20Nobody%20is%20talking%20now%20about%20a%20common%20currency%2C%20he%20said%2C%20the%20focus%20at%20this%20point%20being%20on%20mutual%20trade%2C%20economic%20projects%2C%20and%20investment%20independent%20of%20the%20dollar%2C%20euro%2C%20or%20yen%2C%20of%20the%20system%20controlled%20by%20the%20US%20and%20its%20Western%20allies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20drew%20attention%20to%20the%20BRICS%20project%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bpool%20of%20reserve%20currencies%26quot%3B%20as%20a%20prelude%20to%20the%20planned%20steps%20to%20facilitate%20the%20use%20of%20national%20currencies%2C%20and%2C%20most%20importantly%2C%20to%20form%20an%20alternative%20payment%20system%2C%20on%20which%20the%20finance%20ministers%20and%20central%20bank%20governors%20of%20the%20five%20countries%20have%20been%20charged%20with%20working%20out%20the%20details.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20expansion%20of%20BRICS%20seems%20to%20have%20been%20based%20less%20on%20any%20well-defined%20criteria%20and%20more%20on%20reaching%20a%20quick%20consensus%20on%20which%20countries%20from%20the%2023%20that%20had%20applied%20for%20membership%20would%20be%20acceptable%20to%20all%20the%20five%20existing%20members.%20Four%20of%20the%20six%20new%20members%20are%20from%20the%20same%20broad%20region%20-%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20UAE%2C%20Iran%2C%20and%20Egypt%20-%20which%20shows%20the%20lop-sided%20nature%20of%20the%20expansion.%20Foreign%20Minister%20Lavrov%20has%20validated%20this%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20plus%20value%20they%20would%20bring%20to%20the%20logistics%20projects%20such%20as%20the%20International%20North-South%20Transport%20Corridor%20and%20the%20Northern%20Sea%20Route.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20Lavrov%20played%20down%20the%20significance%20of%20several%20oil-producing%20countries%20joining%20BRICS%2C%20a%20point%20that%20has%20been%20played%20up%20in%20Western%20commentary%20as%20a%20precursor%20to%20a%20potential%20de-dollarisation%20of%20the%20oil%20trade.%20This%20concern%20is%20also%20fed%20by%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20two%20biggest%20consumers%20of%20oil%2C%20China%20and%20India%2C%20are%20BRICS%20members.%20Asked%20whether%20Russia%20had%20proposed%20establishing%20a%20BRICS%20Energy%20Alliance%20or%20a%20BRICS%20Energy%20Bank%2C%20Lavrov%20played%20down%20the%20issue%2C%20noting%20that%20BRICS%20already%20had%20structures%20dealing%20with%20energy%2C%20and%20that%20if%20the%20new%20countries%20joining%20BRICS%20had%20some%20initiatives%20to%20propose%20they%20would%20be%20looked%20at%20and%20carried%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20deciding%20on%20expansion%2C%20no%20consensus%20seems%20to%20have%20been%20reached%20on%20including%20an%20Asian%20country%20even%20though%20Asia%20is%20seen%20as%20the%20centre%20of%20the%20shift%20of%20global%20power%20away%20from%20the%20West.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndonesia%2C%20present%20at%20Johannesburg%2C%20had%20applied%20for%20membership%20but%20apparently%20withdrew%20its%20candidature%20at%20the%20last%20minute.%20China%20would%20have%20opposed%20Vietnam's%20candidature%2C%20and%20that%20of%20Bangladesh%20too%2C%20which%20it%20would%20tie%20up%20with%20that%20of%20Pakistan%2C%20to%20not%20appear%20to%20be%20abandoning%20a%20close%20ally%20as%20well%20as%20to%20deny%20giving%20political%20advantage%20to%20India.%20Ethiopia's%20inclusion%20seems%20surprising%2C%20evidently%20pushed%20by%20China%2C%20although%20Algeria's%20would%20have%20been%20more%20obvious.%20Nigeria%2C%20an%20obvious%20African%20candidate%2C%20did%20not%20apply%20for%20membership%2C%20it%20seems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EForeign%20Minister%20Lavrov%20has%20given%20an%20indication%20of%20the%20criteria%20that%20underlay%20the%20expansion%20decision%2C%20namely%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20weight%2C%20prominence%2C%20and%20importance%20of%20the%20candidates%20and%20their%20international%20standing%26quot%3B%20being%20primary%20factors.%20The%20aim%20was%2C%20according%20to%20him%2C%20to%20%26quot%3Brecruit%20like-minded%20countries%20into%20our%20ranks%20that%20believe%20in%20a%20multipolar%20world%20order%20and%20the%20need%20for%20more%20democracy%20and%20justice%20in%20international%20relations%26quot%3B%20and%20who%20%26quot%3Bchampion%20a%20bigger%20role%20for%20the%20Global%20South%20in%20global%20governance%26quot%3B.%20Ethiopia%2C%20in%20the%20throes%20of%20a%20civil%20war%20and%20reeling%20under%20an%20economic%20crisis%2C%20would%20hardly%20be%20eligible%20under%20this%20criteria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BRICS%20summit%20has%20endorsed%20an%20initiative%20to%20invite%20over%2060%20countries%20to%20engage%20with%20BRICS%20in%20a%20BRICS%20Plus%2FOutreach%20and%20partner%20countries%20format.%20A%20list%20of%20countries%20for%20partner%20country%20status%20will%20be%20worked%20out%20at%20the%20level%20of%20Foreign%20Ministers%20for%20the%202024%20BRICS%20summit%20at%20Kazan%20in%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeculation%20about%20a%20name%20change%20of%20BRICS%2C%20now%20that%20there%20are%2011%20members%20in%20all%2C%20seems%20to%20have%20been%20set%20at%20rest%20for%20the%20moment%20with%20member%20countries%20seemingly%20wanting%20to%20retain%20the%20BRICS%20brand%20name%20to%20also%20emphasise%20continuity%20in%20the%20work%20of%20the%20grouping.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20supported%20the%20BRICS%20expansion.%20We%20have%20very%20friendly%20ties%20with%20all%20the%20new%20members.%20With%20five%20of%20the%20new%20six%20members%2C%20India%20has%20a%20strategic%20partnership.%20The%20leaders%20of%20five%20of%20the%20six%20countries%20have%20been%20chief%20guests%20at%20our%20Republic%20Day%20celebrations.%20With%20Ethiopia%2C%20our%20relations%20have%20been%20traditionally%20strong.%20In%20Africa%2C%20Ethiopia%20is%20the%20largest%20recipient%20of%20long-term%20concessional%20credit%20from%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20world%20now%20has%20the%20G7%20group%20of%20Western%20countries%20plus%20Japan%2C%20the%20G20%20that%20has%20G7%2C%20the%20EU%2C%20and%2012%20countries%20of%20the%20Global%20South%20as%20members.%20Both%20these%20groups%20have%20been%20formed%20at%20the%20initiative%20of%20the%20West.%20The%20expanded%20BRICS%20is%20a%20veritable%20G11%20group%2C%20but%20one%20constituted%20by%20non-western%20powers%2C%20with%20seven%20members%20that%20are%20also%20part%20of%20G20.%20This%20evolution%20in%20group%20formation%20reflects%20the%20changing%20power%20shifts%20that%20are%20taking%20place%20globally%2C%20from%20an%20entirely%20Western%20group%20to%20a%20mixed%20group%20of%20Western%20and%20Global%20South%20countries%2C%20and%2C%20now%20to%20an%20enlarged%20non-Western%20group%2C%20all%20of%20them%20seeking%20to%20address%20the%20issues%20of%20global%20governance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Kanwal%20Sibal%20was%20Foreign%20Secretary%20and%20Ambassador%20to%20Turkey%2C%20Egypt%2C%20France%2C%20and%20Russia%2C%20and%20Deputy%20Chief%20Of%20Mission%20in%20Washington.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693219140000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fa87certg_brics-2023_625x300_23_August_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fthe-importance-of-an-expanded-brics-4335977%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20expansion%20of%20BRICS%20has%20considerable%20geopolitical%20significance.%20It%20is%20a%20consequential%20step%20forward%20in%20changing%20the%20balance%20between%20the%20West%20and%20others%20in%20the%20global%20system.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fthe-importance-of-an-expanded-brics-4335977%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fthe-importance-of-an-expanded-brics-4335977%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fthe-importance-of-an-expanded-brics-4335977%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Protests%20erupt%20in%20Libya%20over%20contact%20with%20Israel%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693219108000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F152F3%2Fproduction%2F_130917768_3b1c31486e6c2045d27e247dc2f5987c676b6fd4.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-africa-66636651%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Libya's%20foreign%20minister%20is%20suspended%20amid%20outrage%20over%20direct%20talks%20with%20historical%20foe%20Israel.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A392%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-africa-66636651%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-