20Red%20Flag.%20Study%20Explains%20Why%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20study%20has%20raised%20concerns%20about%20the%20long-term%20health%20risks%20associated%20with%20night-time%20snoring%20in%20people%20below%20the%20age%20of%2050.%20According%20to%20the%20research%2C%20young%20adults%20who%20snore%20at%20night%20are%20at%20a%20higher%20risk%20of%20having%20a%20stroke%20and%20developing%20heart%20disease%20later%20in%20life%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.independent.co.uk%2Flife-style%2Fhealth-and-families%2Fsnoring-sleep-apnoea-stroke-risk-b2399825.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EIndependent%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20findings%20have%20been%20presented%20at%20the%20European%20Society%20of%20Cardiology%20Congress%20in%20Amsterdam.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMedical%20professionals%20are%20emphasising%20the%20importance%20of%20regarding%20snoring%20as%20a%20significant%20warning%20sign%2C%20particularly%20for%20this%20age%20group.%20The%20study%20revealed%20a%20noteworthy%20statistic%3A%20Young%20adults%20who%20snore%20have%20a%2060%20per%20cent%20higher%20likelihood%20of%20experiencing%20a%20stroke%20in%20middle%20age%2C%20and%20their%20risk%20of%20developing%20a%20heart%20rhythm%20disorder%20increases%20five-fold.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20is%20based%20on%20the%20analysis%20of%20data%20of%20766%2C000%20adults%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20aged%20between%2020%20and%2050.%20Among%20this%20group%2C%207%2C500%20individuals%20suffered%20from%20obstructive%20sleep%20apnea%20-%20a%20condition%20characterised%20by%20breathing%20interruptions%20during%20sleep%2C%20leading%20to%20loud%20snoring%20and%20frequent%20awakenings%20due%20to%20breathing%20struggles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20course%20of%20a%2010-year%20follow-up%20period%2C%20the%20study%20established%20that%20individuals%20with%20sleep%20apnea%20faced%20a%2060%20per%20cent%20elevated%20risk%20of%20stroke%20compared%20to%20those%20who%20snored%20less%20frequently%20or%20not%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20do%20people%20snore%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sleepfoundation.org%2Fsnoring%2Fcommon-causes%5C%22%3ESleep%20Foundation%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20that%20snoring%20occurs%20when%20air%20can't%20flow%20easily%20through%20the%20nasal%20airway%20when%20a%20person%20sleeps.%20The%20airway%20becomes%20narrow%20or%20partially%20blocked%2C%20due%20to%20which%20breathing%20causes%20the%20tissues%20of%20the%20upper%20airway%20to%20vibrate%2C%20resulting%20in%20the%20snoring%20sound.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20a%20sleep%20disorder%2C%20snoring%20can%20be%20caused%20by%20a%20person's%20lifestyle%20or%20habits.%20It%20can%20disrupt%20a%20person's%20sleep%2C%20which%20can%20lead%20to%20other%20health%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20have%20the%20researchers%20said%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExplaining%20the%20findings%2C%20the%20researchers%20said%20that%20people%20who%20are%20below%20the%20age%20of%2050%20and%20snore%20were%20five%20times%20more%20likely%20to%20develop%20atrial%20fibrillation%2C%20a%20heart%20condition%20that%20causes%20irregular%20and%20often%20abnormally%20fast%20heart%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSleep%20apnea%20is%20really%20common%20but%20we%20sort%20of%20ignore%20it%20because%20we%20think%20it's%20trivial%20or%20just%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20a%20nuisance%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Cem%3EIndependent%3C%2Fem%3E%20quoted%20lead%20author%20Professor%20Sanjiv%20Narayan%20of%20Stanford%20University%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUntil%20now%20no%20one's%20really%20shown%20the%20magnitude%20of%20the%20size%20of%20the%20risk%20for%20heart%20diseases.%20That's%20what%20really%20surprised%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693217820000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2019-04%2Fg0qsggro_snoring_625x300_25_April_19.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fsc