across%20his%20point%20of%20view%20in%20an%20uncomplicated%20manner%20during%20the%20interview%2C%20just%20like%20the%20straight%20face%20of%20his%20bat%20when%20he%20hits%20the%20bowler's%20back-drive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20in%20great%20frame%20of%20mind%20and%20prepared%20really%20well%20for%20the%20tournament%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20referring%20to%20the%20last%20edition%2C%20where%20he%20scored%20648%20runs%20with%20an%20unprecedented%20five%20hundreds%20to%20emerge%20as%20the%20highest%20run-getter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20in%20good%20shape%2C%20good%20mindset.%20I%20want%20to%20bring%20that%20back%20and%20I%20have%20time%20to%20do%20that.%20Trying%20to%20recollect%20what%20were%20the%20right%20things%20that%20I%20was%20doing%20before%20the%202019%20World%20Cup%20as%20a%20cricketer%20and%20as%20a%20person.%20I%20want%20to%20revisit%20that%20thought-process%20of%20mine%20personally%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20skipper%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWorld%20Cups%20and%20the%20vagaries%20associated%20with%20the%20results%20can%20change%20a%20lot%20of%20things%20but%20for%20Rohit%2C%20one%20month%20of%20cricket%20can't%20make%20or%20break%20the%20player%20that%20he%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20person%20can't%20change%20overnight%20with%20his%20success%20or%20failures%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20one%20result%20or%20one%20championship%20can%20change%20me%20as%20a%20person.%20I%20have%20not%20changed%20as%20a%20person%20in%20the%20last%2016%20years%20and%20I%20don't%20think%20anything%20needs%20to%20change%20on%20that%20front%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20focus%20will%20be%20on%20how%20I%20can%20achieve%20my%20goals%20in%20the%20next%20two%20months%2C%20for%20me%20and%20my%20team.%20A%20person%20can't%20change%20in%20a%20period%20of%20one%20or%20two%20months.%26quot%3B%20Rohit%20has%20won%20five%20IPL%20titles%20as%20Mumbai%20Indians%20captain%2C%20Asia%20Cup%20as%20India%20captain%20(2018)%20and%20led%20the%20team%20to%20World%20Test%20Championship%20final%20as%20recently%20as%20June%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDo%20you%20ever%20think%20about%20your%20legacy%20in%20Indian%20cricket%20after%20being%20around%20for%2016%20years%3F%20%26quot%3BNo%2C%26quot%3B%20pat%20came%20the%20reply.%20%26quot%3BI%20am%20not%20the%20person%20who%20thinks%20about%20what%20kind%20of%20legacy%20I%20will%20leave%20behind.%20My%20legacy%20will%20be%20for%20people%20to%20judge%20and%20talk%20about.%20Not%20for%20me%20to%20say.%26quot%3B%20He%20has%2030%20ODI%20hundreds%2C%20second%20only%20to%20Virat%20Kohli's%2046.%20Add%2010%20Test%20hundreds%20and%20four%20T20I%20tons.%20A%20total%20of%2017%2C000%20plus%20international%20runs%20aren't%20bad%20numbers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20not%20a%20firm%20believer%20in%20numbers.%20You%20should%20be%20happy%20and%20enjoy%20the%20time%20you%20have%20in-front%20of%20you%2C%20and%20try%20to%20live%20in%20that%20kind%20of%20moment.%20I%20am%20thinking%20about%20what%20gives%20me%20happiness%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20me%2C%20it's%20all%20about%20creating%20memories%20and%20creating%20a%20good%20rapport%20with%20my%20teammates.%20Be%20happy%20in%20whatever%20you%20get%20and%20whatever%20you%20have.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETEAM%20SELECTION%20HEARTBREAKS%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERohit%20will%20have%20an%20unenviable%20task%20of%20telling%20at%20least%20three%20out%20of%2018%20members%20of%20the%20core%20group%20that%20they%20won't%20be%20a%20part%20of%20World%20Cup's%20exclusive%2015.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20sense%20of%20d%C3%A9j%C3%A0%20vu.%20When%20he%20was%2023%2C%20Rohit%20didn't%20get%20a%20look-in%20in%20that%20history-making%20'Class%20of%202011'.%20It%20had%20hurt%2C%20back%20then%20and%20no%20one%20knows%20that%20better%20than%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20picking%20the%20best%20combination%2C%20there%20will%20be%20guys%20who%20will%20miss%20out%20for%20various%20reasons%20and%20Rahul%20bhai%20(Dravid)%20and%20I%20have%20tried%20our%20best%20to%20explain%20to%20the%20players%20why%20they%20are%20not%20in%20the%20squad.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20tried%20to%20communicate%20with%20the%20players%20after%20every%20selection%20and%20playing%20XI%20that%20has%20been%20announced.%20We%20talk%20to%20them%20face%20to%20face%2C%20one-on-one%20why%20they%20have%20not%20been%20picked%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSometimes%2C%20I%20try%20and%20put%20myself%20in%20their%20shoes.%20When%20I%20wasn't%20picked%20in%202011%2C%20it%20was%20such%20a%20heart-breaking%20moment%20for%20me%20and%20I%20felt%20what's%20left%20after%20being%20dropped%20from%20a%20World%20Cup%20squad%3F%26quot%3B%20He%20had%20no%20qualms%20in%20admitting%20that%20at%20times%20his%20and%20Dravid's%20decision%20can%20go%20wrong.%20%26quot%3BMe%2C%20coaches%2C%20and%20selectors%2C%20take%20into%20account%20all%20factors%20like%20opposition%2C%20surfaces%2C%20our%20strengths%2C%20their%20weaknesses%2C%20and%20then%20reach%20a%20common%20ground.%20There%20is%20every%20chance%20that%20we%20will%20not%20be%20perfect%20always.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20few%20individuals%20make%20decisions%2C%20and%20we%20are%20bound%20to%20make%20mistakes%20as%20humans.%20We%20won't%20always%20be%20right%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added%20with%20a%20pause.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERohit%20feels%20that%20he%20%26quot%3Bneeds%20to%20keep%20an%20open%20mind%26quot%3B%20and%20listen%20to%20everyone's%20view%20and%20what%20other%20people%20around%20him%20are%20thinking.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20like%2C%20I%20don't%20like%20this%20person%2C%20so%20I%20am%20dropping%20him.%20Captaincy%20is%20not%20based%20on%20personal%20likes%20and%20dislikes.%20If%20anyone%20misses%20out%2C%20there%20is%20a%20reason%20for%20it.%20If%20you%20are%20the%20unlucky%20one%2C%20we%20can%20do%20nothing.%26quot%3B%20So%20who%20was%20the%20one%20who%20put%20an%20arm%20around%20his%20shoulder%20after%20the%202011%20World%20Cup%20team%20was%20announced%3F%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20sad%20and%20sitting%20in%20my%20room%20and%20didn't%20know%20what%20to%20do%20next.%20I%20remember%20Yuvi%20(Yuvraj%20Singh)%20calling%20me%20to%20his%20room%20and%20taking%20me%20out%20for%20dinner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20explained%20to%20me%20how%20it%20feels%20when%20you%20are%20left%20out.%20He%20told%20me%2C%20'the%20best%20thing%20is%20that%20you%20have%20so%20many%20years%20in-front%20of%20you.%20As%20we%20play%20in%20the%20World%20Cup%2C%20you%20take%20this%20chance%20to%20work%20hard%20on%20your%20game%2C%20skills%20and%20make%20a%20comeback.%20There%20is%20no%20way%20that%20you%20won't%20play%20for%20India%20or%20not%20get%20a%20chance%20to%20play%20in%20the%20World%20Cup'.%26quot%3B%20Skipper%20MS%20Dhoni%20and%20selectors%20felt%20that%20an%20additional%20wrist%20spinner%20in%20Piyush%20Chawla%20would%20be%20more%20useful%20than%20an%20extra%20batter%20back%20in%202011.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20went%20back%20to%20the%20drawing%20board%2C%20worked%20hard%20and%20immediately%20after%20the%20World%20Cup%2C%20I%20made%20a%20comeback%20and%20it%20has%20been%20good%20since%20then.%20Since%20this%20is%20me%2C%20who%20has%20gone%20through%20this%20emotion%2C%20no%20one%20can%20tell%20me%20that%20%26quot%3Beasier%20said%20than%20done%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20faced%20exclusion%20in%20a%20World%20Cup%2C%20and%20I%20know%20how%20it%20exactly%20feels.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBatter%20Rohit%2C%20the%20pull-shots%20and%20the%20risks%20taken%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20there%20is%20one%20shot%20that%20has%20become%20'signature%20Rohit'%20over%20the%20years%2C%20it%20is%20the%20pull-shot%20that%20he%20has%20played%20mostly%20with%20success%2C%20though%20at%20times%20it%20does%20bring%20about%20his%20downfall.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20how%20much%20does%20he%20practice%20the%20pull%20in%20the%20nets%20against%20throwdown%20experts%3F%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20specific%20training%20I%20do%20to%20play%20that%20shot.%20Nobody%20knows%20about%20the%20work%20I%20did%20before%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRaghu%20(Raghvendra)%2C%20Nuwan%20(Senaviratne)%20and%20Daya%20(Garani)%20have%20all%20come%20in%20recent%20years%20and%20I%20have%20been%20playing%20this%20shot%20for%20a%20long%20time%2C%20he%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20three%20support%20staff%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20worked%20on%20this%20shot%20since%20U-17%20and%20U-19%20days.%20Now%20I%20don't%20practice%20this%20shot%20specifically%20during%20the%20training.%20If%20I%20find%20a%20ball%20pitched%20short%2C%20I%20play%20the%20pull.%20The%20bowlers%20are%20not%20just%20going%20to%20bowl%20short%2C%20so%20during%20training%20I%20tell%20bowlers%20to%20bowl%20everything%20in%20a%20manner%20they%20want.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693216920000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-01%2Fgl4t3gko_rohit-sharma-pc-afp_625x300_10_January_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Ficc-cricket-world-cup-2023%2Fcaptaincy-not-based-on-personal-likes-and-dislikes-rohit-sharma-on-world-cup-squad-selection-4335802%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Rohit%20Sharma%20will%20have%20an%20unenviable%20task%20of%20telling%20at%20least%20three%20out%20of%2018%20members%20of%20the%20core%20group%20that%20they%20won't%20be%20a%20part%20of%20World%20Cup's%20exclusive%2015.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A55%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Ficc-cricket-world-cup-2023%2Fcaptaincy-not-based-on-personal-likes-and-dislikes-rohit-sharma-on-world-cup-squad-selection-4335802%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Ficc-cricket-world-cup-2023%2Fcaptaincy-not-based-on-personal-likes-and-dislikes-rohit-sharma-on-world-cup-squad-selection-4335802%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Ficc-cricket-world-cup-2023%2Fcaptaincy-not-based-on-personal-likes-and-dislikes-rohit-sharma-on-world-cup-squad-selection-4335802%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20new%20study%20makes%20it%20official%3A%20Women%20are%20always%20the%20wrong%20age%20for%20employers%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Women%20of%20different%20ages%20pop%20in%20and%20out%20of%20holes%20in%20a%20whack-a-mole%20scenario.%20A%20big%20turquoise%20mallet%20comes%20and%20hits%20some%20of%20the%20women%20on%20the%20head.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e90b08bc26b40019904217%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWomen%20in%20every%20age%20bracket%20reported%20facing%20workplace%20age%20discrimination.%3Cp%3EArantza%20Pena%20Popo%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EJulie%20O'Neill%20spent%20nearly%20three%20decades%20as%20a%20top%20anchor%20for%20Cincinnati's%20WCPO%20news%20station%2C%20but%20early%20last%20year%2C%20her%20career%20took%20a%20gut-wrenching%20turn.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20her%20longtime%20coverage%20of%20the%20Cincinnati%20Bengals%2C%20O'Neill%20was%20passed%20over%20in%20favor%20of%20a%20younger%2C%20male%20colleague%20to%20report%20on%20the%20team's%202022%20Super%20Bowl%20appearance.%20Soon%20after%2C%20she%20said%2C%20she%20began%20receiving%20complaints%20from%20the%20station's%20news%20director%20about%20a%20decline%20in%20her%20performance.%20Puzzled%2C%20she%20began%20recording%20footage%20of%20her%20segments%2C%20hoping%20to%20identify%20and%20correct%20any%20stumbles.%20The%20exercise%20left%20her%20only%20more%20confused.%20Her%20delivery%20seemed%20as%20strong%20as%20ever%2C%20she%20told%20me%2C%20and%20even%20her%20coanchor%20was%20perplexed%20by%20the%20feedback.%20Tensions%20between%20O'Neill%20and%20her%20bosses%20continued%20to%20escalate%2C%20she%20said%2C%20finally%20reaching%20a%20head%20in%20September%20when%20she%20was%20called%20into%20a%20meeting%20with%20management.%20In%20the%20meeting%2C%20O'Neill%20was%20told%20she%20would%20no%20longer%20be%20cohosting%20the%20network's%20morning%20show%20and%20that%20her%20station%20contract%20would%20not%20be%20renewed%20after%20December%2031.%20O'Neill%20recalled%20the%20station's%20general%20manager%20citing%20her%20recent%20on-air%20mention%20of%20a%20colleague's%20recovery%20from%20COVID-19%20%E2%80%94%20which%20the%20colleague%20had%20posted%20openly%20about%20on%20social%20media%20%E2%80%94%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bdisrespectful%26quot%3B%20final%20straw.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUntil%20all%20the%20criticism%20started%2C%20I%20had%20had%20stellar%20performance%20reviews%20and%20was%20never%2C%20ever%20accused%20of%20being%20disrespectful%20or%20making%20people%20uncomfortable%2C%26quot%3B%20O'Neill%20said.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20she%20had%20a%20sneaking%20suspicion%20that%20her%20age%20and%20gender%20might%20have%20played%20a%20role%20in%20the%20abrupt%20turn%20of%20events%2C%20but%20it%20was%20an%20older%2C%20male%20mentor%20who%20made%20her%20see%20the%20connection%20as%20crystal%20clear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20said%20to%20me%2C%20'When%20do%20you%20turn%2055%2C%20Julie%3F'%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20said%2C%20January%209.%20'That's%20interesting%2C'%20he%20said.%20'Nine%20days%20after%20your%20contract%20was%20up%2C%20you%20were%20put%20out%20of%20the%2018-to-54%20demographic'%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.marketingbrew.com%2Fstories%2F2022%2F05%2F26%2Fthe-upfronts-nearly-forgot-about-tv-s-biggest-oldest-audience%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etarget%20age%20bracket%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20network-TV%20ad%20buys.%20(WCPO%20did%20not%20comment%20on%20Julie's%20dismissal%2C%20but%20leadership%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cincinnati.com%2Fstory%2Fnews%2F2023%2F06%2F14%2Fjulie-oneill-says-wcpo-fired-her-age%2F70318914007%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20do%20not%20agree%20with%20many%20statements%20that%20have%20been%20made.%20As%20usual%2C%20we%20don't%20talk%20about%20personnel%20matters%20publicly.%26quot%3B)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20station's%20leadership%20never%20said%20that%20O'Neill's%20age%20was%20a%20factor%20in%20its%20decision-making.%20But%20she%20believes%20they%20didn't%20have%20to.%20In%20her%20view%2C%20%26quot%3Bthey%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20I%20was%20not%20the%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20'prime'%20age%20for%20women%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EO'Neill's%20account%20seems%20shocking%20but%20may%20be%20an%20all-too-familiar%20story%20for%20many%20women%20in%20leadership%20roles.%20A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhbr.org%2F2023%2F06%2Fwomen-in-leadership-face-ageism-at-every-age%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAny%2520age%2520can%2520be%2520stigmatized%2Clower%2520job%2520satisfaction%2520and%2520engagement.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%2C%20qualitative%20survey%20of%20913%20women%3C%2Fa%3E%20across%20four%20disparate%20industries%20%E2%80%94%20law%2C%20faith-based%20nonprofits%2C%20higher%20education%2C%20and%20healthcare%20%E2%80%94%20found%20a%20dismaying%20amount%20of%20age-based%20discrimination%20against%20women%20in%20top%20jobs.%20The%20research%2C%20recently%20published%20in%20Harvard%20Business%20Review%2C%20found%20that%20many%20of%20the%20women%20surveyed%20reported%20being%20at%20the%20receiving%20end%20of%20age-related%20judgment%20that%20implied%20they%20were%20unfit%20for%20the%20job.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20the%20most%20discouraging%20finding%20of%20the%20survey%20was%20that%20the%20ageist%20behavior%20wasn't%20just%20directed%20toward%20one%20age%20cohort.%20For%20women%20under%2040%2C%20ageism%20often%20showed%20up%20in%20the%20form%20of%20%26quot%3Brole%20incredulity%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20higher-ups%20(who%20were%20frequently%2C%20if%20not%20exclusively%2C%20men)%20registering%20surprise%20at%20their%20seniority%2C%20sometimes%20even%20calling%20them%20by%20condescending%20nicknames%20such%20as%20%26quot%3Bkiddo%26quot%3B%20or%20dispensing%20pats%20on%20the%20head.%20(Previous%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1111%2Fjasp.12799%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudies%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20also%20found%20that%20women%20of%20childbearing%20age%20are%20routinely%20passed%20over%20for%20jobs%20or%20promotions%20because%20they%20could%20become%20pregnant.)%20Women%20over%2060%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20reported%20being%20ignored%20altogether%2C%20their%20skills%20overlooked%20and%20their%20experience%20discounted%20in%20favor%20of%20%26quot%3Bfresh%2C%20new%20ideas.%26quot%3B%20Many%20of%20the%20ageist%20dismissals%20echoed%20across%20age%20groups%3A%20Women%20who%20were%20up%20for%20jobs%2C%20promotions%2C%20or%20bonuses%20were%20told%20they%20either%20lacked%20experience%20or%20had%20too%20much%20of%20the%20wrong%20kind.%20Many%20also%20described%20hearing%20ageist%20remarks%20used%20to%20discredit%20other%20women%20who%20were%20up%20for%20professional%20opportunities.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EWhen%20you%20get%20a%20woman%20in%20her%2040s%20or%2050s%20who%20has%20progressed%20in%20her%20career%20and%20is%20probably%20more%20willing%20to%20speak%20her%20mind%2C%20I%20think%20it's%20intimidating%20to%20the%20insecure%20men%20in%20our%20workforce.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EAmy%20Diehl%2C%20a%20gender-equity%20researcher%20and%20one%20of%20the%20coauthors%20of%20the%20new%20report%2C%20wasn't%20surprised%20by%20the%20prevalence%20of%20ageism%20against%20the%20oldest%20and%20youngest%20women%20she%20and%20her%20colleagues%20surveyed.%20But%20she%20was%20taken%20aback%20by%20the%20extent%20to%20which%20middle-aged%20women%20like%20O'Neill%20reported%20experiencing%20age-related%20discrimination%20at%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20men%20get%20to%20their%2040s%20or%2050s%2C%20they're%20considered%20to%20be%20in%20the%20prime%20of%20their%20careers%2C%26quot%3B%20Diehl%20told%20me.%20Women%20of%20the%20same%20age%2C%20however%2C%20continue%20to%20bump%20up%20against%20%26quot%3Bage-related%20constraints.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20a%20grim%20irony%20that%20successful%20women%20in%20midlife%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20are%20so%20often%20made%20to%20feel%20as%20though%20they%20will%20be%20difficult%20or%20distractible%20while%20at%20the%20height%20of%20their%20professional%20prowess.%20The%20researchers%20believe%20that%20this%20happens%20precisely%20%3Cem%3Ebecause%3C%2Fem%3E%20middle-aged%20women%20feel%20they%20have%20less%20to%20lose%20by%20flexing%20their%20hard-earned%20expertise.%20Their%20confidence%2C%20and%20competence%2C%20makes%20them%20threatening.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20get%20a%20woman%20in%20her%2040s%20or%2050s%20who%20has%20progressed%20in%20her%20career%20and%20is%20probably%20more%20willing%20to%20speak%20her%20mind%2C%20I%20think%20it's%20intimidating%20to%20the%20insecure%20men%20in%20our%20workforce%2C%26quot%3B%20Diehl%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20would%20rather%20diminish%20that%20woman%2C%20not%20promote%20her%2C%20keep%20her%20in%20her%20place.%20It's%20not%20that%20they%20don't%20want%20her%20in%20the%20workplace%20%E2%80%94%20they%20just%20want%20her%20in%20a%20role%20that's%20going%20to%20support%20the%20men%20in%20the%20workplace%20and%20not%20compete%20with%20them.%20And%20certainly%20not%20give%20them%20a%20contrary%20opinion.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20survey%2C%20middle-aged%20women%20described%20a%20wide%20variety%20of%20put-downs%20from%20higher-ups%3A%20concerns%20about%20%26quot%3Bmenopause%20issues%26quot%3B%20or%20vague%20accusations%20of%20being%20%26quot%3Bdifficult%20to%20manage.%26quot%3B%20Others%20reported%20being%20told%20that%20their%20phase%20of%20life%20put%20them%20at%20risk%20of%20%26quot%3Bfamily-related%20issues%26quot%3B%20getting%20in%20the%20way%20of%20their%20job%20performance%20%E2%80%94%20a%20line%20of%20commentary%20directed%20against%20professional%20women%20across%20ages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20too%20young%20and%20then%2C%20in%20a%20moment%20in%20time%2C%20you're%20considered%20to%20be%20too%20old%2C%26quot%3B%20Diehl%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20really%20is%20no%20sweet%20spot%20for%20women.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Call%20it%20'sexism'%20because%20that's%20what%20it%20is'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20age%20discrimination%20itself%20may%20not%20strike%20many%20as%20surprising%2C%20the%20fact%20companies%20are%20so%20blatant%20about%20it%20is%20shocking%2C%20especially%20in%20light%20of%20recent%20cultural%20shifts.%20Over%20the%20past%20several%20years%2C%20activist%20movements%20such%20as%20%23MeToo%20and%20Black%20Lives%20Matter%20have%20helped%20raise%20mainstream%20public%20consciousness%20over%20systemic%20sexual%20harassment%20and%20racism.%20%26quot%3BDiversity%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Bequity%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Binclusivity%26quot%3B%20have%20entered%20the%20lexicon%20of%20corporate%20accountability.%20Companies%20have%20dutifully%20launched%20workplace-sensitivity%20seminars%20and%20adjusted%20their%20hiring%20practices%3B%20some%20have%20even%20set%20up%20entire%20human-resources%20departments%20dedicated%20to%20DEI.%20Whether%20or%20not%20these%20initiatives%20have%20proved%20successful%20in%20leveling%20the%20professional%20playing%20field%2C%20a%20majority%20of%20American%20workers%20say%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fsocial-trends%2F2023%2F05%2F17%2Fdiversity-equity-and-inclusion-in-the-workplace%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethey%20appreciate%20the%20effort%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20businesses%20have%20invested%20in%20building%20fairer%20work%20environments%20%E2%80%94%20or%20have%2C%20at%20the%20very%20least%2C%20invested%20in%20elaborate%20lip%20service%20to%20the%20cause%20%E2%80%94%20age%20discrimination%20against%20women%20workers%20not%20only%20persists%20but%20also%20is%20often%20perpetuated%20in%20plain%20view.%20Gendered%20ageism%20may%20even%20be%20the%20last%20acceptable%20form%20of%20workplace%20discrimination%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that's%20even%20truer%20for%20women%20who%20are%20not%20white%20or%20who%20encompass%20multiple%20marginalized%20identities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EThe%20concept%20of%20aging%20is%20something%20that%20is%20socialized%20into%20our%20fabric%20to%20be%20acceptable%20to%20point%20out.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20did%20this%20happen%3F%20The%20likeliest%20answer%20is%20also%20the%20simplest.%20Age%20is%20universal%3B%20everyone%20has%20one.%20Just%20as%20it's%20become%20commonplace%20to%20debate%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-millennial-boomer-gen-x-why-generations-feud-2023-7%5C%22%3Egenerational%20differences%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20compare%20the%20(real%20or%20perceived)%20attributes%20of%20people%20who%20grew%20up%20in%20different%20eras%2C%20people%20feel%20generally%20OK%20discussing%20age%20out%20in%20the%20open.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20concept%20of%20aging%20is%20something%20that%20is%20socialized%20into%20our%20fabric%20to%20be%20acceptable%20to%20point%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20Amber%20L.%20Stephenson%2C%20another%20coauthor%20of%20the%20study%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20just%20so%20much%20more%20comfortable%20taking%20shots%20at%20different%20age%20stages%20or%20career%20stages%2C%20in%20comparison%20with%20other%20types%20of%20bias.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20researchers%20are%20emphatic%20that%20in%20our%20appearance-focused%2C%20age-obsessed%20society%2C%20using%20a%20woman's%20age%20against%20her%20in%20a%20professional%20setting%20is%20a%20mask%20to%20express%20the%20gender%20biases%20we%20have%20yet%20to%20truly%20shake%20as%20a%20culture.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInstead%20of%20'gendered%20ageism%2C'%20we%20can%20just%20call%20it%20'sexism'%20because%20that's%20what%20it%20is%2C%26quot%3B%20Diehl%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeanne%20M.%20Dzubinski%2C%20the%20third%20coauthor%20on%20the%20study%2C%20agreed%3A%20%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20put%20it%20together%20%E2%80%94%20that%20so%20many%20women%2C%20no%20matter%20what%20age%20they%20are%2C%20are%20always%20being%20told%20that%20they're%20not%20the%20right%20age%20%E2%80%94%20then%20what%20we%20see%20is%20it's%20actually%20just%20an%20excuse%20for%20sexism%2C%20period.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'They%20would%20rather%20keep%20her%20in%20her%20place'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EResearch%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpsycnet.apa.org%2FdoiLanding%3Fdoi%3D10.1037%252F0033-295X.109.3.573%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20found%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.buffalo.edu%2Fnews%2Fnews-releases.host.html%2Fcontent%2Fshared%2Fmgt%2Fnews%2Fmen-still-more-likely-than-women-perceived-leaders-study-finds.detail.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erepeatedly%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20public%20imagination%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bleader%26quot%3B%20remains%20static%20%E2%80%94%20and%20regressive.%20Men%20are%20more%20likely%20than%20women%20to%20be%20perceived%20as%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kantar.com%2Fcampaigns%2Freykjavik-index%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eleadership%20material%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.weforum.org%2Freports%2Fglobal-gender-gap-report-2022%2Fin-full%2F2-4-gender-gaps-in-leadership-by-industry-and-cohort%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoverwhelmingly%20more%20likely%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20women%20to%20hold%20leadership%20positions%20across%20virtually%20every%20industry.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20to%20suggest%20that%20all%20is%20hunky-dory%20for%20men%20in%20the%20workforce.%20Much%20has%20been%20written%20about%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2022%2F11%2F04%2F1133586707%2Fboys-men-labor-force-jobs-gender-gap-workforce%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esteady%20decline%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20employment%20among%2025-%20to%2054-year-old%20American%20men%2C%20and%20recent%20surveys%20have%20also%20indicated%20that%20men%20aren't%20immune%20to%20workplace%20ageism.%20In%20one%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hiscox.com%2Fdocuments%2F2019-Hiscox-Ageism-Workplace-Study.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2019%20poll%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20400%20US%20workers%20ages%2040%20and%20older%2C%20more%20men%20than%20women%20reported%20experiencing%20or%20witnessing%20age%20discrimination%20on%20the%20job.%20Research%20has%20also%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.frbsf.org%2Feconomic-research%2Fpublications%2Feconomic-letter%2F2017%2Ffebruary%2Fage-discrimination-and-hiring-older-workers%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20older%20job%20seekers%20face%20age%20discrimination%20regardless%20of%20gender%2C%20despite%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eeoc.gov%2Fstatutes%2Fage-discrimination-employment-act-1967%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E56-year-old%20federal%20law%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20purportedly%20protects%20against%20older-age%20discrimination%20in%20employment.%20And%2C%20as%20always%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fopub%2Freports%2Frace-and-ethnicity%2F2021%2Fhome.htm%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520unemployment%2520rate%2520averaged%25208.6%2Cwas%25206.8%2520percent%2520for%2520Hispanics.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erace%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20identity%20stigmas%20play%20a%20significant%20role%20in%20predicting%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mckinsey.com%2Ffeatured-insights%2Fdiversity-and-inclusion%2Fwomen-in-the-workplace%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhether%20women%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20be%20hired%2C%20promoted%2C%20or%20recognized%20for%20their%20achievements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20undeniable%20that%20workplace%20age%20discrimination%20occurs%20across%20gender%20lines%2C%20but%20the%20qualitative%20experiences%20surfaced%20by%20Diehl%2C%20Stephenson%2C%20and%20Dzubinski%20help%20paint%20a%20picture%20of%20how%20an%20open%20culture%20around%20age%20discrimination%20can%20ultimately%20end%20up%20fueling%20good%2C%20old-fashioned%20sexism.%20The%20researchers%20urge%20women%20at%20the%20receiving%20end%20of%20superficial%20or%20immaterial%20workplace%20criticisms%20to%20recognize%20that%20age-related%20feedback%20%E2%80%94%20or%20negative%20character-based%20appraisals%20such%20as%20%26quot%3Bbeing%20difficult%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20reflect%20on%20the%20shortcomings%20of%20their%20superiors%20than%20on%20their%20performance.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EO'Neill%2C%20the%20Cincinnati%20anchor%2C%20offers%20herself%20as%20a%20case%20in%20point.%20After%20departing%20from%20WCPO%2C%20she%20refused%20to%20sign%20the%20nondisclosure%20agreement%20that%20would%20entitle%20her%20to%20a%20job%20severance%20package%20and%2C%20instead%2C%20recently%20published%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbiauto-61631-20%26h%3Da2c1f8adf94