-japan-agree-to-postpone-head-of-japan-coalition-partner-visit-chinese-ministry%2Farticleshow%2F103131019.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fchina-japan-agree-to-postpone-head-of-japan-coalition-partner-visit-chinese-ministry%2Famp_articleshow%2F103131019.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fchina-japan-agree-to-postpone-head-of-japan-coalition-partner-visit-chinese-ministry%2Famp_articleshow%2F103131019.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Specify%20Scope%20of%20Power%20for%20Proposed%20Fact-Checking%20Unit%E2%80%99%3A%20Editors%20Guild%20to%20Karnataka%20Government%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F20160312%2FUntitled-design-23-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Editors%20Guild%20India%20on%20Sunday%20(August%206)%20expressed%20concerns%20over%20Karnataka%20government%E2%80%99s%20decision%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eto%20set%20up%20a%20%E2%80%98fact-checking%20unit%E2%80%99%20to%20monitor%20%E2%80%98fake%20news%E2%80%99%20on%20social%20media%20platforms.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20per%20Karnataka%E2%80%99s%20IT%20%26amp%3B%20BT%20Minister%2C%20Priyank%20Kharge%2C%20%E2%80%9Cposts%20and%20reports%20that%20are%20tagged%20as%20fake%20by%20the%20fact%20checking%20unit%20will%20be%20taken%20down%2C%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cif%20required%2C%20the%20government%20can%20also%20take%20penal%20measures%20under%20relevant%20provisions%20of%20the%20IPC.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Guild%20has%20already%20filed%20a%20petition%20in%20the%20Bombay%20high%20court%20challenging%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fit-rules-amendment-legal-complications%5C%22%3Eamendments%20to%20the%20IT%20Rules%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20allow%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20set%20up%20a%20%E2%80%98fact%20checking%20unit%E2%80%99%2C%20have%20the%20sole%20authority%20on%20deciding%20if%20a%20post%20is%20fake%20or%20not%20and%20order%20it%20to%20be%20taken%20down.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Bombay%20high%20court%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fbombay-hc-extends-stay-on-it-rules-that-allow-union-govt-to-fact-check-social-media%5C%22%3Eextended%20the%20stay%20on%20the%20IT%20Rules%20in%20June%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20two%20new%20petitions%20were%20filed%20by%20the%20Editors%20Guild%20of%20India%20and%20the%20Association%20of%20Indian%20Magazines%2C%20challenging%20the%20constitutional%20validity%20of%20the%20provisions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDuring%20the%20hearings%20in%20July%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fbombay-high-court-it-rules-fake-news-excessive%5C%22%3Ecourt%20had%20remarked%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20one%20cannot%20%E2%80%9Cbring%20a%20hammer%20to%20kill%20an%20ant%E2%80%9D%20while%20calling%20the%20IT%20Rules%20excessive.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fbombay-high-court-it-rules-fake-news-excessive%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Can%E2%80%99t%20Bring%20Hammer%20To%20Kill%20Ant%E2%80%99%3A%20Bombay%20HC%20Says%20IT%20Rules%20on%20%E2%80%98Fake%E2%80%99%20News%20May%20Be%20Excessive%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWhile%20admittedly%20there%20is%20a%20problem%20of%20misinformation%20and%20fake%20news%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20online%20space%2C%20efforts%20to%20check%20such%20content%20have%20to%20be%20by%20independent%20bodies%20that%20are%20not%20under%20the%20sole%20purview%20of%20the%20government%2C%20lest%20they%20become%20tools%20to%20clamp%20down%20on%20voices%20of%20dissent%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20Guild%20said%20in%20its%20latest%20statement.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20jour