pointment%2C%20as%20his%20country%20finished%20the%20championships%20without%20a%20medal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20first%20world%20championships%20in%201983%2C%20communist%20East%20Germany%20topped%20the%20medals%20table.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3EWith%20AFP%20inputs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693209660000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2F0fdl8ggo_neeraj-and-arshad_625x300_28_August_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fathletics%2Fas-neeraj-chopra-bags-worlds-gold-arshad-nadeem-makes-big-olympics-prediction-4335395%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India's%20Neeraj%20Chopra%20and%20Pakistan's%20Arshad%20Nadeem%20completed%20a%201-2%20finish%20at%20the%20Men's%20Javelin%20Throw%20final%20in%20World%20Athletics%20Championships.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A265%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fathletics%2Fas-neeraj-chopra-bags-worlds-gold-arshad-nadeem-makes-big-olympics-prediction-4335395%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fathletics%2Fas-neeraj-chopra-bags-worlds-gold-arshad-nadeem-makes-big-olympics-prediction-4335395%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fathletics%2Fas-neeraj-chopra-bags-worlds-gold-arshad-nadeem-makes-big-olympics-prediction-4335395%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Shoddy%20Drafting%20Has%20Left%20the%20Government's%20New%20Criminal%20Bills%20With%20Glaring%20Errors%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28124704%2FUntitled-design-3-2.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Union%20government%20has%20introduced%20three%20Bills%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20to%20completely%20replace%20the%20three%20major%20criminal%20laws%20in%20operation%20since%20centuries%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act%2C%201872%2C%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%2C%201860%2C%20and%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure%2C%201973.%20Together%2C%20these%20laws%20define%20a%20citizen%E2%80%99s%20interaction%20with%20the%20criminal%20justice%20system.%20Hence%2C%20one%20would%20have%20thought%20that%20any%20attempts%20at%20their%20complete%20overhaul%20would%20be%20a%20serious%20undertaking.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20let%20alone%20the%20substantive%20changes%20made%20by%20them%2C%20their%20incomprehensible%20drafting%20gives%20rise%20to%20more%20confusion%20than%20anything%20that%20existed%20previously%20under%20the%20colonial%20laws.%20The%20provisions%20of%20the%20Bharatiya%20Sakshya%20Bill%2C%202023%2C%20which%20replaces%20the%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act%2C%201872%2C%20and%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20Bill%2C%202023%20which%20replaces%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%2C%201860%20have%20glaring%20drafting%20errors%20and%20inconsistencies.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprsindia.org%2Ffiles%2Fbills_acts%2Fbills_parliament%2F2023%2FBHARATIYA_SAKSHYA_BILL%2C%25202023.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Bharatiya%20Sakshya%20Bill%2C%202023%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20replaces%20the%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act%2C%201872%2C%20and%20yet%2C%20the%20Evidence%20Act%20sees%20perhaps%20the%20least%20number%20of%20substantive%20changes%20brought%20in%20by%20the%20new%20Bill%20when%20compared%20to%20the%20changes%20made%20to%20the%20rules%20contained%20in%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%2C%201860%20and%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure%2C%201973.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20The%20Sakshya%20Bill%20makes%20at%20least%20two%20major%20and%20welcome%20changes%20to%20the%20provisions%20earlier%20contained%20in%20the%20Evidence%20Act%3A%20(i)%20it%20streamlines%20the%20rules%20on%20electronic%20evidence%3B%20and%20(ii)%20expands%20the%20scope%20of%20secondary%20evidence.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fknow-the-three-new-criminal-bills-whats-new-and-whats-old%5C%22%3EKnow%20The%20Three%20New%20Criminal%20Bills%3A%20What%E2%80%99s%20New%20and%20What%E2%80%99s%20Old%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20for%20the%20latter%2C%20the%20Bill%20usefully%20plugs%20a%20loophole%20of%20the%20Evidence%20Act%20by%20accounting%20for%20written%20admissions%20as%20secondary%20evidence.%20This%20apart%2C%20it%20leaves%20the%20essential%20premises%20of%20what%20constitute%20%E2%80%98relevant%E2%80%99%20facts%20to%20be%20considered%20by%20courts%20%E2%80%93%20as%20declared%20by%20the%20Evidence%20Act%20%E2%80%93%20unchanged.%20The%20other%20chapters%20of%20the%20Evidence%20Act%2C%20such%20as%20those%20on%20witnesses%2C%20burdens%20of%20proof%2C%20oral%20and%20documentary%20evidence%2C%20presumptions%2C%20etc.%20remain%20largely%20the%20same%20as%20in%20the%20Evidence%20Act.%20This%20in%20itself%20is%20a%20testament%20to%20the%20time-tested%20rules%20of%20logic%20crystallised%20in%20the%20Evidence%20Act%20centuries%20before%20the%20current%20%E2%80%98decolonisation%E2%80%99%20efforts%20sought%20to%20revisit%20the%20three%20major%20criminal%20laws.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20even%20though%20the%20substantive%20changes%20made%20to%20the%20Evidence%20Act%20are%20not%20many%2C%20the%20confusing%20drafting%20and%20misplaced%20provisos%20existing%20in%20the%20current%20form%20of%20the%20Sakshya%20Bill%20raise%20more%20questions%20than%20they%20answer.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Take%20for%20example%20the%20case%20of%20section%20165%20of%20the%20Bill%20dealing%20with%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20power%20to%20order%20production%20of%20documents.%20Sub-sections%20(1)%20and%20(2)%20of%20the%20Bill%20deal%20with%20the%20broad%20contours%20of%20this%20power%20and%20the%20sub-section%20(3)%20deals%20with%20the%20specific%20power%20to%20give%20directions%20to%20translators.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20proviso%20that%20is%20attached%20to%20sub-section%20(3)%2C%20however%2C%20is%20unmeaning%20in%20reference%20to%20it.%20It%20carves%20out%20an%20exception%20to%20the%20court%E2%80%99%20s%20power%20to%20direct%20production%20of%20documents%20in%20favour%20of%20privileged%20documents%20between%20ministers%20and%20the%20President%20of%20India%20and%20should%20instead%20have%20been%20placed%20next%20to%20sub-sections%20(1)%20or%20(2)%20where%20the%20broader%20scope%20of%20the%20power%20is%20outlined%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20the%20provision%20on%20interpreters.%20If%20this%20seems%20like%20a%20pedantic%20pointing%20out%20of%20an%20error%20with%20no%20substantive%20consequence%2C%20then%20the%20new%20provision%20on%20confessions%20under%20section%2023%20of%20the%20Bill%20raises%20the%20stakes%20involved%20with%20poor%20drafting.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUnder%20the%20Evidence%20Act%2C%20confessions%20made%20to%20police%20officers%2C%20whether%20in%20their%20custody%20or%20outside%2C%20were%20considered%20inadmissible%20in%20courts%20by%20virtue%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F494844%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esection%2025%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20widely%20recognised%20policy%20behind%20this%20exclusion%2C%20as%20also%20stated%20by%20Sir%20James%20Stephen%20who%20drafted%20the%20Act%2C%20was%20to%20disincentivize%20coercion%20often%20used%20by%20police%20officers%20to%20extract%20confessions.%20If%20evidence%20of%20the%20confession%20taken%20by%20the%20police%20could%20anyway%20not%20be%20used%20in%20courts%2C%20there%20would%20be%20no%20incentive%20to%20use%20torture%20to%20extract%20them%20%E2%80%93%20or%20so%20was%20the%20rationale.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFollowing%20broadly%20the%20same%20logic%2C%20the%20Evidence%20Act%20through%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F387768%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esection%2026%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20additionally%20made%20inadmissible%2C%20confessions%20made%20in%20police%20custody%20to%20anyone%20other%20than%20a%20police%20office%2C%20unless%20in%20the%20immediate%20presence%20of%20a%20magistrate.%20However%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1312051%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esection%2027%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20the%20Act%20which%20immediately%20followed%20these%20two%20provisions%2C%20made%20specific%20parts%20of%20such%20confessions%20known%20as%20%E2%80%98discovery%20statements%E2%80%99%20admissible%20in%20courts%20%E2%80%93%20regardless%20of%20the%20restrictions%20outlined%20above%20%E2%80%93%20if%20an%20object%20was%20discovered%20further%20to%20such%20statements%20(such%20as%20the%20weapon%20of%20the%20offence).%20This%20exception%20for%20discovery%20statements%20has%20been%20widely%20criticised%20as%20diluting%20the%20original%20disincentive%20against%20using%20coercion%20to%20extract%20confessions.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fhow-consultative-was-the-framing-of-the-three-criminal-law-bills-really%5C%22%3EHow%20Consultative%20Was%20the%20Framing%20of%20the%20Three%20Criminal%20Law%20Bills%2C%20Really%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20all%2C%20if%20police%20can%E2%80%99t%20use%20the%20confession%20of%20guilt%20by%20an%20accused%2C%20it%20may%20still%20resort%20to%20coercion%20so%20that%20it%20can%20use%20that%20part%20of%20the%20statement%20which%20could%20lead%20it%20to%20the%20discovery%20of%20the%20object.%20Nonetheless%2C%20through%20a%20long%20line%20of%20decisions%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20recognised%20(such%20as%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F481284%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EState%20of%20UP%20v%20Deoman%20Upadhyaya%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1329788%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520trial%2520court%2520held%2520that%2Cpresumed%2520to%2520be%2520the%2520thief.%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EMohmed%20Inayatullah%20v%20State%20of%20Maharashtra%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20and%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F924340%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAghnoo%C2%A0%20Nagesia%20v%20State%20of%20Bihar%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20etc.)%20that%20the%20discovery%20statement%20exception%20operated%20both%20to%20confessions%20made%20to%20police%20officers%20under%20section%2025%2C%20and%20those%20made%20to%20anyone%20other%20than%20a%20police%20officer%20but%20in%20police%20custody%20under%20section%2026.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESection%2023%20of%20the%20Bill%20incorporates%20all%20the%20above%20three%20provisions%20of%20the%20Evidence%20Act%20as%20separate%20clauses%20of%20one%20section.%20However%2C%20as%20it%20is%20currently%20worded%2C%20it%20appears%20that%20the%20proviso%20for%20discovery%20statements%20has%20been%20attached%20only%20to%20the%20second%20case%20of%20confessions%20in%20police%20custody%2C%20and%20not%20to%20the%20first%20case%20of%20confessions%20made%20to%20police%20officers%20generally.%20This%20means%20that%20the%20bar%20under%20the%20first%20category%2C%20i.e.%20confessions%20made%20to%20a%20police%20officer%20has%20been%20made%20absolute%20and%20even%20the%20discovery%20statement%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20be%20admissible%20in%20case%20of%20such%20confessions.%20This%20certainly%20brings%20back%20the%20disincentive%20attached%20to%20confessions%20made%20to%20police%20officers%20with%20full%20force.%20This%20would%20be%20a%20welcome%20step%20towards%20enhancing%20the%20safeguards%20of%20accused%20persons.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20it%20is%20not%20necessarily%20clear%20whether%20this%20indeed%20was%20the%20intention.%20This%20is%20not%20least%20because%20it%20would%20unsettle%20decades%20of%20jurisprudence%20on%20confessions%20as%20laid%20down%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20but%20also%20because%20the%20proviso%20could%20have%20been%20intended%20to%20operate%20to%20both%20the%20categories%20of%20confessions%20and%20is%20mistakenly%20attached%20only%20to%20the%20second%20one.%20Given%20the%20example%20of%20section%20165%20above%2C%20this%20being%20a%20result%20of%20simply%20bad%20drafting%20cannot%20be%20ruled%20out.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENonetheless%2C%20it%20has%20substantive%20consequences%20for%20an%20important%20safeguard%20against%20coercion%20in%20the%20rules%20of%20evidence.%20Take%20another%20example%20of%20the%20presumptions%20as%20to%20certain%20documents%20and%20electronic%20records%20contained%20in%20sections%2092%20and%2093%20of%20the%20Bill%2C%20which%20say%20the%20%E2%80%98Explanations%E2%80%99%20attached%20to%20sections%2083%20and%2084%20will%20also%20apply%20to%20the%20former%20two%20sections%3B%20except%2C%20no%20such%20%E2%80%98Explanations%E2%80%99%20are%20to%20be%20found%20in%20the%20latter%20provisions.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20unclear%20why%20the%20Bills%20have%20been%20rushed%20in%20without%20proper%20proof-reading%20on%20basic%20instances%20of%20drafting%20errors.%20These%20drafting%20errors%20are%20not%20unique%20to%20the%20Sakshya%20Bill.%20Take%20another%20curious%20case%20from%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fpdf_upload%2Fthe-bharatiya-nyaya-sanhita-2023-485731.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EBharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20Bill%202023%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20which%20is%20intended%20to%20replace%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%2C%201860.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20IPC%20provided%20that%20if%20an%20offence%20is%20committed%20under%20an%20intoxicated%20state%20of%20mind%2C%20then%20such%20intoxication%20was%20a%20defence%20for%20reduced%20sentencing%20if%20the%20intoxication%20happened%20against%20the%20accused%E2%80%99s%20knowledge%20or%20against%20their%20will.%20This%20is%20popularly%20known%20as%20the%20defence%20of%20%E2%80%98involuntary%20intoxication%E2%80%99%20under%20the%20Code.%20Now%20consider%20the%20strange%20formulation%20under%20section%2023%20of%20the%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20Bill%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%98Nothing%20is%20an%20offence%20which%20is%20done%20by%20a%20person%20who%2C%20at%20the%20time%20of%20doing%20it%2C%20is%2C%20by%20reason%20of%20intoxication%2C%20incapable%20of%20knowing%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20act%2C%20or%20that%20he%20is%20doing%20what%20is%20either%20wrong%2C%20or%20contrary%20to%20law%3B%20unless%20that%20the%20thing%20which%20intoxicated%20him%20was%20administered%20to%20him%20without%20his%20knowledge%20or%20against%20his%20will.%E2%80%99%20By%20using%20the%20word%20%E2%80%9Cunless%E2%80%9D%20instead%20of%20%E2%80%9Cprovided%20that%E2%80%9D%2C%20this%20provision%20seems%20to%20suggest%20the%20converse%20of%20the%20involuntary%20intoxication%20defence%20%E2%80%93%20that%20unless%20one%20is%20involuntarily%20intoxicated%2C%20they%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20be%20considered%20as%20having%20committed%20the%20offence.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccordingly%2C%20it%20leads%20to%20an%20absurd%20conclusion%20where%20voluntary%20intoxication%20becomes%20a%20valid%20defence%20in%20criminal%20law%2C%20and%20not%20involuntary%20intoxication!%20Similarly%2C%20see%20the%20Explanation%20attached%20to%20section%20150%20of%20the%20Sanhita%20which%20substitutes%20the%20offence%20of%20sedition%20under%20the%20IPC.%20It%20appears%20that%20the%20drafters%20of%20the%20Explanation%20forgot%20to%20complete%20the%20sentence%20itself%2C%20and%20we%20are%20left%20with%20a%20so-called%20%E2%80%98Explanation%E2%80%99%20that%20does%20everything%20but%20explain%20this%20vital%20provision%20which%20is%20now%20to%20replace%20the%20law%20on%20sedition.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETo%20bring%20in%20major%20changes%20to%20laws%20which%20have%20been%20in%20place%20for%20centuries%20could%20certainly%20be%20driven%20by%20genuine%20reasons%20to%20decolonize%20the%20criminal%20laws.%20However%2C%20the%20number%20of%20instances%20of%20poor%20drafting%20of%20these%20provisions%20betrays%20a%20sense%20of%20frivolity%20with%20which%20this%20major%20undertaking%20has%20been%20carried%20out.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Chairman%20of%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20has%20referred%20the%20Bills%20to%20the%20Standing%20Committee%20on%20Home%20Affairs.%20It%20is%20hoped%20that%20these%20errors%20can%20be%20clarified%20and%20the%20rule%20on%20admissibility%20of%20confessions%20is%20stated%20with%20more%20certainty.%20Criminal%20laws%2C%20more%20than%20any%20other%20substantive%20law%2C%20most%20directly%20impact%20our%20liberties%20and%20fundamental%20rights.%20The%20task%20of%20their%20reform%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20performed%20lightly.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EPranav%20Verma%20is%20assistant%20professor%20(law)%20at%20the%20National%20Law%20School%20of%20India%20University%2C%20Bengaluru.%20Views%20expressed%20are%20personal.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693209646000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28124704%2FUntitled-design-3-2.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fcriminal-bills-drafting-shoddy-sakshya-nyay-sanhita-ipc-evidence%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Criminal%20laws%2C%20more%20than%20any%20other%20substantive%20law%2C%20most%20directly%20impact%20our%20liberties%20and%20fundamental%20rights.%20The%20task%20of%20their%20reform%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20performed%20lightly.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fcriminal-bills-drafting-shoddy-sakshya-nyay-sanhita-ipc-evidence%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Drones%2C%20AI%2C%203D%20Training%3A%20New%20Playbook%20To%20Curb%20Monster%20Wildfires%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20planet%20continues%20to%20warm%2C%20so%20grows%20the%20list%20of%20countries%20impacted%20by%20wildfires.%20Turkey%2C%20Greece%20and%20Spain%20have%20all%20dealt%20with%20blazes%20this%20year%2C%20and%20this%20month's%20wildfire%20in%20Hawaii%20killed%20at%20least%20115%20and%20razed%20the%20town%20of%20Lahaina.%20Canada%20is%20in%20the%20throes%20of%20a%20historic%20wildfire%20season%2C%20with%20more%20than%2015%20million%20hectares%20burned.%20Officials%20there%20are%20scrutinizing%20the%20limits%20of%20traditional%20firefighting%20tactics.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Europe%2C%20the%20fastest-warming%20continent%20due%20to%20climate%20change%2C%20firefighters%20are%20exploring%20new%20ways%20to%20battle%20monster%20blazes.%20Emergency%20and%20disaster%20management%20crews%20are%20deploying%20drones%20than%20can%20detect%20fires%20earlier%20and%20are%20even%20reviving%20traditional%20practices%20such%20as%20using%20sheep%20and%20goats%20to%20graze%20the%20grass.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20some%20of%20the%20more%20innovative%20wildfire%20solutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDrones%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDrones%20are%20becoming%20ubiquitous%20on%20the%20front%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDomingos%20Xavier%20Viegas%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20Coimbra%20University%20in%20Portugal%20who%20specializes%20in%20wildland%20fire%20behavior%2C%20says%20departments%20across%20Europe%20are%20using%20drone%20technology%20to%20map%20vegetation%2C%20identify%20high-risk%20areas%2C%20track%20wildfires%2C%20collect%20data%20and%20deliver%20last-mile%20water%20deposits%20during%20wildfires.%20Larger%20drones%2C%20some%20of%20them%20amphibious%2C%20are%20also%20being%20developed%20to%20act%20as%20aerial%20tankers%20or%20hose%20bearers.%20These%20firefighting%20robots%20can%20spray%20water%20and%20fire-retardant%20chemicals%20over%20longer%20distances%20and%20larger%20areas.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20can%20also%20save%20the%20lives%20of%20firefighters%20who%20otherwise%20have%20to%20get%20%26quot%3Bso%20close%20to%20the%20fires%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Kenneth%20Geipel%2C%20founder%20of%20Danish%20drone%20company%20Robotto%20Co.%20Geipel%20started%20Robotto%20in%202019%20after%20seeing%20%C2%A0the%20devastation%20left%20by%20record%20wildfires%20in%20Sweden%2C%20Greece%20and%20California%20a%20year%20earlier.%20He%20felt%20firefighters%20lacked%20the%20data%20needed%20to%20map%20and%20tackle%20blazes%20at%20the%20earliest%20stages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20satellite%20imagery%20comes%20with%20delays%2C%20drones%20can%20in%20real%20time%20identify%20smoke%20or%20heat%20signatures%2C%20warn%20fire%20control%20authorities%20and%20calculate%20the%20position%2C%20size%20and%20intensity%20of%20a%20blaze%2C%20Geipel%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EArtificial%20intelligence%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20this%20new%20information%20requires%20more%20data-processing.%20Drone%20sensors%20capture%20more%20data%20than%20is%20humanly%20possible%20to%20process%20in%20real%20time%20without%20using%20AI%20tools%2C%20Geipel%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20the%20World%20Economic%20Forum%20launched%20an%20AI%20and%20machine%20learning%20initiative%20called%20FireAId.%20The%20pilot%20project%2C%20started%20in%20Turkey%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20country's%20worst-ever%20wildfires%20in%202021%2C%20showed%20these%20tools%20can%20reduce%20response%20time%20and%20risk%20to%20firefighters.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E3D%20training%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETraining%20regimens%20for%20firefighters%20are%20also%20getting%20more%20high-tech%20and%20more%20collaborative%20as%20departments%20in%20different%20countries%20compare%20best%20practices.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Catalonia%2C%20the%20Pau%20Costa%20Foundation%20has%20created%20a%20three-dimensional%20system%20that%20allows%20trainees%20and%20fire%20teams%20to%20run%20through%20emergency%20wildfire%20scenarios.%20This%20so-called%20%26quot%3Bdigital%20sandbox%26quot%3B%20helps%20students%20to%20visualize%20the%20behavior%20of%20a%20forest%20fire%20and%20practice%20fire-management%20strategies%2C%20preparation%20that%20can%20be%20particularly%20helpful%20for%20firefighters%20in%20northern%20European%20countries.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20something%20that%20major%20cosmopolitan%20cities%20like%20London%20had%20never%20experienced%20before%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Sami%20Goldbrom%2C%20a%20group%20commander%20at%20the%20London%20Fire%20Brigade%20(LFB).%20%26quot%3BBut%20it%20looks%20likely%20that%20we're%20going%20to%20be%20experiencing%20them%20for%20the%20foreseeable%20future.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEngland%20saw%20its%20worst%20wildfire%20season%20last%20year%3A%20July%2019%2C%202022%2C%20was%20LFB's%20busiest%20day%20since%20World%20War%20II.%20The%20LFB%20has%20since%20set%20up%20training%20connections%20with%20Australia%2C%20Greece%20and%20Spain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVegetation-clearing%20robots%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20way%20to%20tackle%20wildfires%20is%20to%20prevent%20them%20in%20the%20first%20place.%20That's%20why%20selective%20culling%20of%20trees%20and%20smaller%20plants%20is%20an%20important%20aspect%20of%20reducing%20wildfire%20risk.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEnter%20vegetation-clearing%20robots%2C%20which%20can%20remove%20potential%20wildfire%20fodder.%20Such%20devices%20are%20being%20developed%20and%20will%20work%20alongside%20drones%2C%20Viegas%20says.%20The%20drones%20map%20out%20the%20high-risk%20areas%20from%20above%2C%20and%20the%20mechanical%20foot%20soldiers%20weed%20out%20vegetation%20in%20those%20patches.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFire%20Flocks%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUntil%20vegetation-clearing%20robots%20become%20more%20commercially%20viable%2C%20some%20fire-management%20bodies%20are%20relying%20on%20an%20age-old%20pastoral%20technique%3A%20inviting%20sheep%20and%20goats%20to%20do%20the%20same%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Catalonia%2C%20so-called%20Fire%20Flocks%20-%20sheep%20or%20goats%20that%20graze%20on%20forest%20floors%20to%20clean%20up%20vegetation%20-%20are%20making%20a%20comeback.%20A%20project%20to%20revive%20this%20tradition%20was%20initiated%20in%202016%2C%20starting%20with%20a%20small%20pilot%20of%20just%2048%20hectares%20in%20the%20Baix%20Emporda%20region%20of%20Catalonia.%20By%202022%2C%20it%20had%20expanded%20to%20651%20hectares.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECatalonia%20is%20one%20of%20the%20few%20places%20on%20the%20planet%20where%20fire-prevention%20measures%20have%20reversed%20an%20increase%20in%20blazes%2C%20according%20to%20Marc%20Castellnou%2C%20a%20wildland%20fire%20incident%20commander%20and%20analyst%20with%20the%20Catalan%20Fire%20Service.%20During%20the%201990s%2C%20about%2013%2C500%20hectares%20burned%20in%20wildfires%20every%20year%20-%20roughly%201%25%20of%20the%20region's%20forests%2C%20he%20says.%20Since%20then%20it%20has%20fallen%20to%20between%201%2C200%20and%201%2C500%20hectares%20each%20year%2C%20on%20average.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20the%20best%20mitigation%20strategies%20don't%20negate%20the%20urgency%20of%20curbing%20greenhouse%20gas%20emissions%20to%20prevent%20fire%20risk%20from%20getting%20even%20worse.%20%26quot%3BIf%20a%20fire%20has%20a%20burning%20power%20of%20more%20than%2010%2C000%20kilowatts%20per%20square%20meter%2C%20it%20can't%20be%20extinguished%20no%20matter%20how%20many%20resources%20we%20put%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20Castellnou%20says.%20Some%20of%20Europe's%20wildfires%20in%20recent%20years%20have%20hit%20six%20times%20that%20intensity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693209180000%2C%22vi