droom%20without%20being%20stopped%20or%20interrogated.%20He%20had%20set%20up%20a%20bed%20in%20what%20seemed%20to%20be%20the%20living%20room%20of%20his%20house%20in%20Cuttack%20city.%20%E2%80%9CSo%2C%20this%20is%20how%20a%20poet%20lives%E2%80%9D%2C%20I%20thought.%20%E2%80%9CA%20carefree%20life%20that%20only%20loneliness%20can%20supply%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJayanta%20%3Cem%3EBabu%3C%2Fem%3E%20opened%20his%20eyes.%20A%20current%20of%20excitement%20seemed%20to%20pass%20through%20his%20body%20that%20instantly%20shook%20off%20decades%20from%20his%20frame.%20He%20had%20spotted%20my%20companion%20on%20this%20afternoon%20excursion%2C%20the%20well-known%20translator%20and%20literary%20critic%20Jatin%20Nayak.%20With%20surprising%20agility%2C%20Jayanta%20Babu%20swung%20his%20feet%20down%20and%20stood%20up.%20He%20was%20soon%20bustling%20about%20the%20room%2C%20rummaging%20among%20teacups%2C%20indicating%20the%20chairs%20we%20could%20use%2C%20amidst%20a%20flow%20of%20happy%20chatter.%20None%20of%20us%2C%20perhaps%20even%20Jayanta%20Babu%2C%20knew%20that%20he%20would%20pass%20away%20only%20a%20few%20weeks%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-width%3D%5C%22550%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%20data-dnt%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CAll%20the%20poetry%20there%20is%20in%20the%20world%3Cbr%3E%20appears%20to%20rise%20out%20of%20the%20ashes.%3Cbr%3E%20The%20ash%20sits%20between%20us%20and%3Cbr%3E%20puts%20its%20arms%20across%20our%20shoulders.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20poet%20ever%20dies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELong%20live%20Jayanta%20Mahapatra%20(1928-2023).%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FJayantaMahapatra%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23JayantaMahapatra%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FOdia%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23Odia%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FPoetry%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23Poetry%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FndOJjx4wtR%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FndOJjx4wtR%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Anand%20ST%20Das%20(%40anandstdas)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fanandstdas%2Fstatus%2F1695862287255715938%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EAugust%2027%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20afternoon%2C%20Jatin%20Nayak%20introduced%20me%20as%20the%20grandson%20of%20a%20Communist%20Party%20member%2C%20who%20had%20passed%20away%20twenty%20years%20ago%20but%20was%20still%20fondly%20remembered%20by%20old%20timers%20in%20Odisha.%20%E2%80%9COf%20course%2C%20I%20know%20who%20that%20is%E2%80%9D%2C%20Jayanta%20Babu%20said%20of%20my%20grandfather.%20A%20rooted%20poet%2C%20he%20was%20equally%20interested%20in%20discussing%20the%20comparatively%20unspectacular%20world%20of%20Cuttack%20as%20he%20was%20describing%20his%20experiences%20at%20the%20hallowed%20International%20Writing%20Program%20at%20Iowa%2C%20where%20he%20participated%20in%20the%20year%201976-77.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMahapatra%20gave%20me%20a%20piercing%20look%20and%20went%20back%20to%20his%20animated%20conversation%20with%20Nayak%20and%20his%20son%2C%20who%20was%20also%20present.%20Throughout%20the%20afternoon%2C%20Jayanta%20Babu%20never%20directed%20a%20remark%20or%20a%20question%20specifically%20towards%20me.%20But%20his%20sentences%20invited%20me%20into%20his%20conversation.%20%E2%80%9CI%20am%20reading%20Tolstoy%20again%2C%20at%20the%20age%20of%2095%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20said%20to%20us.%20%E2%80%9CI%20find%20I%20read%20it%20so%20differently%20today%20than%20I%20did%20decades%20ago%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20noticed%20another%20book%20that%20lay%20on%20the%20bedside%20table.%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Man%20Outside%3C%2Fem%3E%20by%20Wolfgang%20Borchert%20seemed%20to%20be%20a%20significant%20choice%20by%20Jayanta%20Babu%20that%20raised%20many%20questions%20in%20my%20mind.%20A%20nonagenarian%20poet%20reading%20the%20book%20written%20by%20a%20writer%2C%20who%20had%20died%20at%20the%20age%20of%2026.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTr%C3%BCmmerliteratur%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20almost%20mumbled%20under%20his%20breath%2C%20giving%20the%20book%20a%20quick%20glance%2C%20while%20not%20even%20looking%20at%20me.%20Later%2C%20I%20looked%20up%20the%20word%2C%20which%20was%20the%20only%20one%20he%20said%20to%20me%20over%20an%20entire%20afternoon.%20The%20German%20term%2C%20meaning%20rubble%20literature%2C%20represented%20a%20literary%20movement%20that%20rose%20after%20World%20War%20II.%20It%20featured%20stories%20of%20loss%20and%20rejection%20%E2%80%93%20lives%20that%20had%20turned%20to%20rubble.%20But%20I%20suspected%20that%20as%20a%20poet%20and%20humanitarian%2C%20Mahapatra%20was%20more%20drawn%20to%20the%20kinds%20of%20pain%20that%20loss%20can%20produce.%20Mahapatra%20had%20taught%20physics%20for%20a%20living%2C%20but%20as%20a%20poet%20he%20was%20obsessed%20with%20human%20experience%2C%20especially%20pain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-width%3D%5C%22550%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%20data-dnt%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ERIP%20Jayanta%20Mahapatra.%20Wonderful%20man%2C%20great%20poet.%20Many%20vivid%20memories%20of%20visiting%20him%20at%20his%20home%20in%20Cuttack.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2Ff8XbbCC4mF%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2Ff8XbbCC4mF%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Amitav%20Ghosh%20(%40GhoshAmitav)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FGhoshAmitav%2Fstatus%2F1695873520729837684%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EAugust%2027%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20several%20instances%20when%20he%20had%20written%20or%20spoken%20about%20his%20own%20life%2C%20Mahapatra%20had%20implied%20that%20pain%20is%20the%20metaphor%20of%20time.%20It%20is%20pain%20that%20keeps%20the%20past%20fresh%20in%20our%20minds.%20Happy%20and%20joyous%20memories%20can%20only%20be%20cherished%20because%20they%20offer%20some%20respite%20from%20painful%20memories.%20Mahapatra%E2%80%99s%20boyhood%2C%20in%20his%20own%20words%2C%20was%20defined%20by%20a%20viscerally%20painful%20incident%20when%20he%20was%20around%20nine%20years%20of%20age.%20In%20this%20case%2C%20the%20crippling%20memory%20of%20the%20pain%20stayed%20with%20him%20for%20at%20least%20half%20a%20century.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJayanta%20Mahapatra%20was%20educated%20in%20Cuttack%20city%E2%80%99s%20iconic%20Stewart%20School%2C%20a%20British%20missionary%20run%20institution.%20Though%20a%20stellar%20student%2C%20Mahapatra%20was%20not%20liked%20by%20a%20section%20of%20his%20own%20classmates%2C%20who%20happened%20to%20be%20superior%20to%20him%20in%20wealth%20and%20bodily%20strength.%20He%20had%20once%20recalled%20in%20vivid%20terms%20how%20his%20bigger%20classmates%20crushed%20his%20spirit%20through%20raw%20power%20and%20brutality.%20They%20had%20cornered%20the%20frail%20and%20young%20looking%20Mahapatra%20during%20lunch%20break.%20Dragging%20him%20against%20his%20will%2C%20they%20had%20pinned%20him%20on%20a%20desk%2C%20while%20rough%20hands%20started%20pulling%20down%20his%20shorts.%20They%20wanted%20to%20verify%20whether%20his%20body%E2%80%99s%20most%20private%20parts%20appeared%20as%20young%20as%20the%20boy%20himself%20did.%20Fifty%20years%20later%2C%20Mahapatra%20had%20written%20about%20the%20incident%20for%20an%20American%20publication.%20%E2%80%9CI%20had%20been%20stripped%20down%20to%20the%20wound%20of%20sex%E2%80%A6My%20body%20has%20grown%2C%20a%20snake%20curling%20about%20its%20pain%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-width%3D%5C%22550%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%20data-dnt%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EJayanta%20Mahapatra%20(22%20October%201928-%2027%20August%202023)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPoets%20never%20die%20as%20long%20as%20we%20read%20them