ing%20economic%20connection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20widow%20of%20the%20wealthiest%20man%20in%20Ireland%20at%20the%20time%20wanted%20to%20help%20starving%20farmers%20during%20the%20Irish%20famine%20in%20the%201740s%2C%20but%20she%20did%20not%20want%20to%20give%20out%20food%20for%20free.%20Instead%2C%20she%20had%20these%20famine-struck%20farmers%20build%20her%20the%20folly%20to%20earn%20their%20keep%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftravelleague.net%2Firelands-famine-follies%2F%5C%22%3ETravel%20League%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcuriousireland.ie%2Fconollys-folly%2F%5C%22%3ECurious%20Ireland.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20fake%20castle%20ruins%20soon%20became%20a%20hotspot%20for%20entertainment%20for%20the%20rich.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E6.%20White%20sugar%20was%20once%20a%20prized%20possession%2C%20and%20nowhere%20was%20its%20status%20more%20on%20display%20than%20in%20the%20white%20icing%20on%20a%20cake.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222610%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Wedding%20cake.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5e31be41e0e1442c197f7e36%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223239%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWedding%20cake.%3Cp%3EJOHN%20STILLWELL%C2%A0%2F%C2%A0Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it%20had%20been%20imported%20since%20the%20Middle%20Ages%2C%20it%20was%20only%20in%20the%20sixteenth%20century%20that%20sugar%20became%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.smithsonianmag.com%2Farts-culture%2Fthe-strange-history-of-the-wedding-cake-1-63011094%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewidely%20available%20in%20England.%3C%2Fa%3E%20And%20the%20whiter%20the%20sugar%2C%20the%20more%20refined%20%E2%80%93%20and%20expensive%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was.%20White%20icing%20on%20a%20cake%20meant%20no%20cost%20had%20been%20spared%20in%20the%20making.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoon%20enough%2C%20pure%20white%20bridal%20cakes%20became%20a%20symbol%20of%20status%2C%20Carol%20Wilson%20wrote%20in%202005%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgastronomica.org%2F2005%2F05%2F05%2Fwedding-cake-a-slice-history%2F%5C%22%3EGastronomica%20essay%20titled%20%26quot%3BWedding%20Cake%3A%20A%20Slice%20of%20History.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201840%2C%20when%20Queen%20Victoria%20married%20Prince%20Albert%2C%20the%20cake%20was%20piped%20with%20white%20icing%2C%20which%20thereafter%20was%20known%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nationalgeographic.co.uk%2Fhistory-and-civilisation%2F2021%2F06%2Fqueen-victorias-300-pound-wedding-cake-set-a-big-new-trend-for-brides%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Broyal%20icing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20The%20multi-tiered%20cake%20measured%20over%20nine%20feet%20in%20circumference.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20then-Princess%20Elizabeth%20married%20Prince%20Philip%20in%201947%2C%20the%20cake%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.smithsonianmag.com%2Farts-culture%2Fthe-strange-history-of-the-wedding-cake-1-63011094%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estood%3C%2Fa%3E%20nine%20feet%20tall%20and%20weighed%20about%20a%20quarter%20of%20a%20tonne.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E7.%20In%20the%20late%202010s%2C%20urban%20chickens%20became%20the%20Teslas%20of%20Silicon%20Valley's%20tech%20elite.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225365%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Indoor%20farm%20of%20hens%20that%20lay%20eggs.%20-%20stock%20photo%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e78f09a7adf7001907442c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224023%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIndoor%20farm%20of%20hens%20that%20lay%20eggs.%20-%20stock%20photo%3Cp%3EKARRASTOCK%2F%20Getty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202018%2C%20an%20unusual%20fad%20gripped%20Silicon%20Valley's%20tech%20elite%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fnews%2Fbusiness%2Fwp%2F2018%2F03%2F02%2Ffeature%2Fthe-silicon-valley-elites-latest-status-sy