0that's%20led%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmade-pizza-rat-viral-youtube-video-still-making-money-2022-12%5C%22%3Eviral%20memes%20like%20Pizza%20Rat%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20experts%20say%20people%2C%20not%20rodents%2C%20are%20behind%20the%20persistent%20infestation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20role%20as%20director%20of%20rodent%20mitigation%2C%20Kathleen%20Corradi%20%E2%80%94%20a%20former%20school%20teacher%20credited%20with%20creating%20the%20city's%20Zero%20Waste%20Schools%20initiative%20while%20she%20worked%20at%20the%20Department%20of%20Education%20%E2%80%94%20has%20been%20given%20a%20Sisyphean%20task%3A%20To%20reduce%2C%20by%20whatever%20means%20necessary%2C%20New%20York's%20rat%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECorradi%20was%20appointed%20after%20residents%20reported%20almost%203.2%20million%20rat%20sightings%20to%20the%20city's%20311%20service%20request%20line%20last%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-york-rat-czar-kathleen-corradi-rats-are-not-enemy-2023-4%5C%22%3EInsider%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%20The%20rats%20are%20so%20iconic%20to%20the%20city%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fnyc-tourists-rat-tours-see-citys-mascots-2023-8%5C%22%3Etourists%20go%20on%20walking%20tours%3C%2Fa%3E%20just%20to%20catch%20a%20glimpse%20of%20them.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRats%20are%20a%20symptom%20of%20systemic%20issues%2C%20including%20sanitation%2C%20health%2C%20housing%2C%20and%20economic%20justice%2C%26quot%3B%20Corradi%20said%20when%20her%20hiring%20was%20announced.%20%26quot%3BAs%20the%20first%20director%20of%20rodent%20mitigation%2C%20I'm%20excited%20to%20bring%20a%20science-%20and%20systems-based%20approach%20to%20fight%20rats.%20New%20York%20may%20be%20famous%20for%20the%20Pizza%20Rat%2C%20but%20rats%2C%20and%20the%20conditions%20that%20help%20them%20thrive%20will%20no%20longer%20be%20tolerated%20%E2%80%94%20no%20more%20dirty%20curbs%2C%20unmanaged%20spaces%2C%20or%20brazen%20burrowing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20for%20the%20New%20York%20Mayor's%20Office%20and%20Department%20of%20Sanitation%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20Insider's%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20city%20has%20historically%20focused%20on%20population%20control%20methods%2C%20including%20brutal%20spring%20traps%20and%20hazardous%20poisons%20to%20keep%20the%20pests%20at%20bay.%20Scientists%20even%20developed%20a%20rat%20birth%20control%20to%20be%20used%20in%20baits%2C%20according%20to%20an%20essay%20published%20Sunday%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F08%2F27%2Fopinion%2Fnyc-rats-eric-adams.html%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Jason%20Munshi-South%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20biology%20at%20Fordham%20University.%20However%2C%20it%20was%20too%20costly%20and%20ineffective%20for%20real-world%20usage.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20despite%20years%20of%20trying%20to%20shoo%20away%20or%20kill%20the%20rodents%2C%20which%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fwhat-attracts-mice-2018-12%5C%22%3Ecarry%20and%20spread%20parasites%20and%20disease%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20rats%20in%20the%20city%20are%20still%20frequently%20seen%20on%20the%20subway%2C%20in%20trash%20cans%2C%20and%20simply%20walking%20down%20the%20street%20in%20search%20of%20their%20next%20meal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERats%20aren't%20the%20real%20enemy%2C%20Munshi-South%20and%20other%20experts%2C%20including%20Michael%20Parsons%2C%20an%20urban%20rat%20researcher%20and%20visiting%20scholar%20at%20Fordham%20University%2C%20agree.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EParsons%20previously%20told%20Insider%20the%20%26quot%3Breal%20city%20rats%26quot%3B%20are%20%26quot%3Bthe%20men%20and%20women%20of%20bureaucracy%20and%20their%20two-and-a-half%20centuries%20of%20bad%20practice.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMs.%20Corradi%20needs%20to%20change%20to%20science-supported%20steps%20rather%20than%20unproven%2C%20'gimmicky'%20approaches%2C%26quot%3B%20Parsons%20said%2C%20giving%20examples%20like%20relying%20on%20unproven%20methods%20like%20composting%20to%20reduce%20the%20presence%20of%20rats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20city%20officials%20should%20study%20rodent%20biology%2C%20conduct%20cleaning%20during%20the%20day%20while%20the%20rats%20are%20less%20active%2C%20and%20develop%20a%20more%20efficient%20waste%20disposal%20system%20citywide%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMunshi-South%20also%20argues%20that%20people%20are%20the%20problem%20%E2%80%94%20more%20than%20rats%2C%20which%20are%20just%20seeking%20food%20out%20of%20survival%C2%A0%20%E2%80%94%20could%20ever%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20rats%20to%20go%20away%2C%20everyone%20in%20the%20city%20%E2%80%94%20plus%20our%20restaurants%2C%20schools%2C%20grocers%20%E2%80%94%20must%20be%20willing%20to%20address%20the%20fundamental%20issue%20of%20food%20waste%2C%26quot%3B%20Munshi-South%20wrote%20for%20NYT.%20%26quot%3BNew%20Yorkers%20waste%20roughly%206.5%20million%20pounds%20every%20day%2C%20which%20amounts%20to%20as%20much%20as%20a%20pound%20per%20person.%20To%20really%20have%20fewer%20rats%2C%20New%20York%20norms%20of%20takeout%20and%20eating%20outside%20would%20have%20to%20change.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20a%20citywide%20population%20of%20over%208%20million%20people%2C%20according%20to%202022%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.census.gov%2Fquickfacts%2Ffact%2Ftable%2Fnewyorkcitynewyork%2FPST045222%5C%22%3ECensus%3C%2Fa%3E%20records%2C%20that%20challenge%20may%20prove%20more%20difficult%20than%20Corradi%20bargained%20for%20when%20she%20accepted%20the%20%24155%2C000-per-year%20position.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20may%20have%20been%20prepared%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20rats%2C%20but%20Parsons%20said%20the%20key%20to%20her%20success%20will%20be%20to%20%26quot%3Bunderstand%20that%20rat%20control%20begins%20by%20changing%20people's%20habits%2C%20hygiene%2C%20and%20expectations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca